1
00:01:34,791 --> 00:01:36,500
[HARUHI]
Here we g--!

2
00:01:36,583 --> 00:01:37,541
[HARUHI groaning]

3
00:01:40,791 --> 00:01:45,791
[KYON] My ride aint swift,
'cause my gears won't shift.

4
00:01:45,875 --> 00:01:48,125
[sighs] What a pain.

5
00:01:52,708 --> 00:01:53,916
[KYON]
I'm home!

6
00:01:54,000 --> 00:01:55,375
Man. Was it cold out--

7
00:01:55,458 --> 00:01:57,625
[KYON'S SISTER]
Hi-yah! Welcome back attack!

8
00:01:57,708 --> 00:01:59,791
[KYON groans] A simple greeting
that suddenly transforms

9
00:01:59,875 --> 00:02:01,416
into a malicious attack.

10
00:02:01,500 --> 00:02:03,000
You've got great skills, sis.

11
00:02:03,083 --> 00:02:04,833
Loser. You went off by yourself

12
00:02:04,916 --> 00:02:07,208
and had fun without me,
didn't you?!

13
00:02:07,291 --> 00:02:09,750
Poor Shamisen was forced
to play with me all day.

14
00:02:09,833 --> 00:02:12,250
He says you suck,
so that was payback for him.

15
00:02:12,333 --> 00:02:13,625
For Shamisen?!

16
00:02:15,666 --> 00:02:18,458
[KYON groans]

17
00:02:18,541 --> 00:02:20,250
So tired.

18
00:02:20,333 --> 00:02:23,541
I probably should've
just taken her with me.

19
00:02:26,041 --> 00:02:28,625
[MIKURU]
Teeter-totter, teeter-totter...

20
00:02:28,708 --> 00:02:31,166
Huh? I think Kyon's
tryin' to fall asleep.

21
00:02:31,250 --> 00:02:34,125
We'll have him count sheep
so he can get to sleep faster.

22
00:02:34,208 --> 00:02:35,583
C'mon! Jump!

23
00:02:35,666 --> 00:02:37,750
Get up and jump through that
hoop so he can count you!

24
00:02:37,833 --> 00:02:42,083
I can't sleep while
she's being tortured!

25
00:02:44,375 --> 00:02:47,208
Uh... Where am I?

26
00:02:47,291 --> 00:02:51,041
Let's see. I was lying in bed,
started counting sheep...

27
00:02:51,125 --> 00:02:55,666
Played the straight man,
then after that... Oh, I get it.

28
00:02:55,750 --> 00:02:57,541
I'm dreaming!

29
00:02:57,625 --> 00:03:01,375
I'm really sorry, Miss Sheep...
I fell asleep on you.

30
00:03:01,458 --> 00:03:03,750
[KOIZUMI chuckles]
You're such a bad person.

31
00:03:03,833 --> 00:03:04,916
Huh?

32
00:03:05,000 --> 00:03:06,458
Hello, I'll be playing
Mount Fuji today.

33
00:03:06,541 --> 00:03:08,000
[KYON]
Whoa! Weirdo in the house!

34
00:03:08,083 --> 00:03:10,666
What? Is that any way
to greet your friend?

35
00:03:10,750 --> 00:03:13,083
It's just, that if I admit
you're Koizumi, I'm pretty sure

36
00:03:13,166 --> 00:03:15,000
a lot of people are
gonna get mad at me.

37
00:03:15,083 --> 00:03:16,916
Who cares? It's just
a dream, isn't it?

38
00:03:17,000 --> 00:03:18,833
[KYON] Thanks for a reminder,
Captain Obvious!

39
00:03:18,916 --> 00:03:20,208
Do you like the outfit?

40
00:03:20,291 --> 00:03:22,125
It's good luck to have a
New Year's dream with either

41
00:03:22,208 --> 00:03:23,833
Fuji, a hawk, or an eggplant.

42
00:03:23,916 --> 00:03:24,708
[KYON]
Who asked you?!

43
00:03:24,791 --> 00:03:26,166
Why are you getting so upset?

44
00:03:26,250 --> 00:03:28,750
Now that I'm Fuji,
the best omen you can get,

45
00:03:28,833 --> 00:03:31,375
I'm going to bring you
bunches of joy and happiness.

46
00:03:31,458 --> 00:03:34,125
It freaks me out to see you
in that get-up, smiling at me.

47
00:03:34,208 --> 00:03:35,416
[KOIZUMI]
Naturally.

48
00:03:35,500 --> 00:03:37,166
And I seriously doubt
that you could bring me

49
00:03:37,250 --> 00:03:38,916
bunches of joy and happiness.

50
00:03:39,000 --> 00:03:40,583
[KOIZUMI]
What?! That's impossible.

51
00:03:40,666 --> 00:03:41,708
I can't believe you figured out

52
00:03:41,791 --> 00:03:43,416
that I'm just a
plain old mountain.

53
00:03:43,500 --> 00:03:44,875
How did you know
I couldn't bring you

54
00:03:44,958 --> 00:03:46,083
bunches of joy and happiness?!

55
00:03:46,166 --> 00:03:48,083
You're not Mount Fuji?!

56
00:03:49,375 --> 00:03:51,458
[KYON]
Grow big!

57
00:03:52,333 --> 00:03:54,916
[KOIZUMI]
He's turned into a shinjin!

58
00:03:55,000 --> 00:03:56,916
[KYON sighs]

59
00:03:57,000 --> 00:04:01,375
[KYON] Don't say anything
to anyone about this!

60
00:04:03,250 --> 00:04:04,791
I got a little carried away.

61
00:04:04,875 --> 00:04:07,208
I'm glad you changed
back to your normal self.

62
00:04:07,291 --> 00:04:09,625
I was gonna try yelling
at you to snap you out of it,

63
00:04:09,708 --> 00:04:11,666
but I guess that would've
been really weird.

64
00:04:11,750 --> 00:04:14,416
Believe me. You couldn't be
any weirder in that outfit.

65
00:04:14,500 --> 00:04:15,791
[KOIZUMI]
Oh? You think?

66
00:04:15,875 --> 00:04:18,583
Maybe I should go and find
the other two omens now.

67
00:04:18,666 --> 00:04:20,333
[KOIZUMI] The hawk's been
up there this whole time.

68
00:04:20,416 --> 00:04:22,000
[KYON]
That thing's a hawk?!

69
00:04:24,041 --> 00:04:24,875
Hi, I'm a hawk.

70
00:04:24,958 --> 00:04:26,791
[KYON]
No way, you're a crane!

71
00:04:27,500 --> 00:04:31,041
[TSURUYA] Kyon... you shouldn't
judge a person by how they look.

72
00:04:31,125 --> 00:04:33,916
Inside this crane
beats the heart of a hawk!

73
00:04:35,833 --> 00:04:37,500
You're still a crane though.

74
00:04:37,583 --> 00:04:39,000
[TSURUYA]
Well, yeah.

75
00:04:39,083 --> 00:04:41,000
So where's the eggplant?

76
00:04:41,083 --> 00:04:43,875
With the way things are going, I
bet it's around here somewhere.

77
00:04:43,958 --> 00:04:45,125
Let me trying calling her.

78
00:04:45,208 --> 00:04:46,250
[KYON]
You have a cell phone?!

79
00:04:46,333 --> 00:04:47,333
[phone rings]

80
00:04:47,416 --> 00:04:49,541
[KYON]
Huh? What's that doing there?

81
00:04:51,625 --> 00:04:53,208
Hello there, Miss Nagato.

82
00:04:53,291 --> 00:04:55,166
Ah-ha, so Nagato's the eggplant.

83
00:04:55,250 --> 00:04:56,250
[KOIZUMI grunts]

84
00:04:56,333 --> 00:04:57,708
It was lying on
the ground over here.

85
00:04:57,791 --> 00:05:00,000
You should've told us
that you found Miss Nagato.

86
00:05:00,083 --> 00:05:00,958
Good for you.

87
00:05:01,041 --> 00:05:02,833
I was talking about the phone.

88
00:05:02,916 --> 00:05:04,833
[KOIZUMI]
So was I. Look at the strap.

89
00:05:04,916 --> 00:05:05,916
Why? What's on the--?

90
00:05:06,000 --> 00:05:08,500
--I am the eggplant.
--It's her!

91
00:05:08,583 --> 00:05:11,750
[KYON] Okay, so, now that
I've found everyone...

92
00:05:11,833 --> 00:05:13,000
Well...

93
00:05:13,083 --> 00:05:14,000
[BOTH]
What?!

94
00:05:14,083 --> 00:05:15,208
[KYON]
I'm done! I wanna wake up!

95
00:05:15,291 --> 00:05:16,583
We can't really
help you with that.

96
00:05:16,666 --> 00:05:17,833
[KYON]
What's that supposed to mean?!

97
00:05:17,916 --> 00:05:20,500
It means, we can't
really help you with that.

98
00:05:20,583 --> 00:05:22,833
But, you did manage to find
the only person among us

99
00:05:22,916 --> 00:05:25,250
who's ever been able to help
you in the past, didn't you?

100
00:05:25,333 --> 00:05:27,000
Nagato! Yeah, that's right!

101
00:05:27,083 --> 00:05:29,791
You know when you wink at me,
that also sorta freaks me out.

102
00:05:29,875 --> 00:05:31,333
[KOIZUMI]
I know.

103
00:05:31,416 --> 00:05:34,666
Okay, Nagato! Tell me how to
wake up from this crazy dream!

104
00:05:34,750 --> 00:05:37,875
Go to sleep here, and
wake up in the real world.

105
00:05:37,958 --> 00:05:38,875
That's it?

106
00:05:38,958 --> 00:05:40,125
That's it.

107
00:05:42,000 --> 00:05:44,916
[birds chirping]

108
00:05:45,000 --> 00:05:46,791
[KYON exhales]

109
00:05:46,875 --> 00:05:49,583
[MIKURU]
Teeter-totter, teeter-totter...

110
00:05:49,666 --> 00:05:52,166
Huh? I think Kyon's
tryin' to fall asleep.

111
00:05:52,250 --> 00:05:55,000
We'll have him count sheep
so he can get to sleep faster.

112
00:05:55,083 --> 00:05:56,458
C'mon! Jump!

113
00:05:56,541 --> 00:05:58,583
Get up and jump through that
hoop so he can count you!

114
00:05:58,666 --> 00:06:00,875
Stop torturing her like that!

115
00:06:03,041 --> 00:06:05,500
[KYON sighs]

116
00:06:26,041 --> 00:06:27,625
Here we g--!

117
00:06:27,708 --> 00:06:28,958
[HARUHI groaning]

118
00:06:31,458 --> 00:06:39,708
[bell chimes]

119
00:06:39,791 --> 00:06:45,916
[KYON humming]

120
00:06:46,000 --> 00:06:48,083
[KYON]
Knock, knock. Anyone home?

121
00:06:48,166 --> 00:06:49,416
[HARUHI]
Come in.

122
00:06:49,500 --> 00:06:50,041
Hey.

123
00:06:50,125 --> 00:06:51,666
I'm bored!

124
00:06:51,750 --> 00:06:54,666
Why haven't any clients
walked through the door?!

125
00:06:54,750 --> 00:06:56,708
I'm bored! Bored! Bored!

126
00:06:56,791 --> 00:07:00,541
Bored, bored, bored!

127
00:07:00,625 --> 00:07:03,583
[HARUHI yelling]
Uh?

128
00:07:03,666 --> 00:07:05,958
[KYON]
Same old Haruhi. What a spaz.

129
00:07:06,041 --> 00:07:07,166
Geez.

130
00:07:07,250 --> 00:07:09,500
I'm just gonna stay
like this and fidget.

131
00:07:09,583 --> 00:07:10,875
--[door opens]
--Would you calm down?

132
00:07:10,958 --> 00:07:13,416
--[HARUHI] Fidget. Fidget...
--[KYON] Someone's here.

133
00:07:16,666 --> 00:07:18,625
[KYON] It's your fault
we lost that one.

134
00:07:18,708 --> 00:07:20,208
[HARUHI]
Dammit!

135
00:07:20,291 --> 00:07:21,250
[HARUHI groans]

136
00:07:22,416 --> 00:07:23,833
[HARUHI]
That hurt.

137
00:07:23,916 --> 00:07:25,875
[KYON]
I bet. Can I go home?

138
00:07:27,083 --> 00:07:28,833
[knocks]

139
00:07:28,916 --> 00:07:30,166
Hey.

140
00:07:30,250 --> 00:07:33,083
Hm? Just you, huh?

141
00:07:33,166 --> 00:07:35,625
[VOICE IN GAME]
Oh, no! It hurts so good.

142
00:07:35,708 --> 00:07:41,666
[grunts] Are you... playing
what I think you're playing?

143
00:07:44,291 --> 00:07:47,833
[yells]
So, you like that stuff?

144
00:07:47,916 --> 00:07:48,958
You know it.

145
00:07:49,041 --> 00:07:51,333
Oh. Okay then.

146
00:07:51,416 --> 00:07:52,958
[KYON] They say hobbies
are good for you,

147
00:07:53,041 --> 00:07:54,708
and I'm really
happy you found one.

148
00:07:54,791 --> 00:07:56,916
But, um, you might
want to use headphones

149
00:07:57,000 --> 00:07:58,333
so you don't bother anyone.

150
00:07:58,416 --> 00:08:00,708
That's what all the
good kids do, anyway.

151
00:08:03,833 --> 00:08:04,666
[KYON]
Hm?

152
00:08:04,750 --> 00:08:06,500
--Play with me.
--No, I'm good!

153
00:08:07,916 --> 00:08:09,666
I... can't... move my body.

154
00:08:09,750 --> 00:08:10,958
Ha, ha.

155
00:08:11,041 --> 00:08:13,916
What will Haruhi Suzumiya
do after I kill you?

156
00:08:14,000 --> 00:08:15,625
[KYON]
What are you doing, Asakura?

157
00:08:15,708 --> 00:08:17,166
Now, you die.

158
00:08:19,583 --> 00:08:20,750
[YUKI]
I forf--

159
00:08:22,458 --> 00:08:24,833
[KYON]
Nagato, you all right?

160
00:08:24,916 --> 00:08:25,916
I'm fine.

161
00:08:26,000 --> 00:08:28,208
[KYON]
Really? You don't look so hot.

162
00:08:28,291 --> 00:08:31,875
You won this time. But if you
think this means you're safe,

163
00:08:31,958 --> 00:08:36,375
think again. I'm the weakest
of the Four Radical Lords.

164
00:08:36,458 --> 00:08:38,833
And you'll be meeting
the others soon enough.

165
00:08:38,916 --> 00:08:40,083
[KYON]
What a generic set-up.

166
00:08:40,166 --> 00:08:41,416
[ASAKURA]
Then, there are three others

167
00:08:41,500 --> 00:08:43,375
who rule over the first four...

168
00:08:43,458 --> 00:08:44,833
The butler did it.

169
00:09:05,125 --> 00:09:06,666
[HARUHI]
Here we g--!

170
00:09:06,750 --> 00:09:07,708
[HARUHI groaning]

171
00:09:10,791 --> 00:09:11,666
[door opens]

172
00:09:11,750 --> 00:09:13,666
[MIKURU]
Sorry I'm late.

173
00:09:14,875 --> 00:09:17,208
Huh? Where is everybody?

174
00:09:17,291 --> 00:09:20,125
Uh... Hm.

175
00:09:20,208 --> 00:09:21,958
Mikuru, are you watching?!

176
00:09:22,041 --> 00:09:24,208
Waugh!

177
00:09:24,291 --> 00:09:26,291
Time for your favorite
local quiz show!

178
00:09:26,375 --> 00:09:28,541
Are you smarter
than the SOS Brigade?

179
00:09:28,625 --> 00:09:31,041
Now, let's introduce
today's contestants!

180
00:09:31,125 --> 00:09:33,250
First up, we have Yuki Nagato!

181
00:09:33,333 --> 00:09:34,541
[bell dings]

182
00:09:34,625 --> 00:09:36,541
[HARUHI] Uh, Yuki,
don't press the button yet.

183
00:09:36,625 --> 00:09:38,041
And next is... that guy.

184
00:09:38,125 --> 00:09:41,000
Uh! Say my name!
It's only one syllable.

185
00:09:41,083 --> 00:09:43,375
Hey, Koizumi,
give me the camera.

186
00:09:43,458 --> 00:09:45,375
This is our cameraman, Koizumi.

187
00:09:45,458 --> 00:09:46,666
Pleased to meet you!

188
00:09:46,750 --> 00:09:48,416
[KYON]
You introduced the cameraman?!

189
00:09:48,500 --> 00:09:51,166
Let's move on to
the quiz, shall we?

190
00:09:51,250 --> 00:09:53,166
The first topic is the universe.

191
00:09:53,250 --> 00:09:55,250
There's nothing
local about that!

192
00:09:55,333 --> 00:09:56,708
Shut it, Kyon.

193
00:09:58,083 --> 00:10:00,833
Oh, okay. If you
really want local topics

194
00:10:00,916 --> 00:10:02,625
then I'll just
change the question.

195
00:10:02,708 --> 00:10:04,458
Let's see... Hm...

196
00:10:04,541 --> 00:10:05,583
Oh!

197
00:10:05,666 --> 00:10:07,041
What's the name of
that dog over there?

198
00:10:07,125 --> 00:10:08,583
[KYON]
Too random!

199
00:10:08,666 --> 00:10:11,125
You have 30 minutes to answer
the question, starting now.

200
00:10:11,208 --> 00:10:13,333
[KYON]
Too long!

201
00:10:13,416 --> 00:10:15,791
[HARUHI] Time's up.
May I have your answers?

202
00:10:15,875 --> 00:10:16,875
[KYON]
Uh!

203
00:10:16,958 --> 00:10:18,250
[bell dings]

204
00:10:18,333 --> 00:10:19,458
[HARUHI] You only have
to press the button

205
00:10:19,541 --> 00:10:22,000
during the lightning
round, okay?

206
00:10:22,083 --> 00:10:24,500
The correct answer is...

207
00:10:24,583 --> 00:10:27,666
[KYON]
You took so long they left.

208
00:10:27,750 --> 00:10:30,666
Good try, but the correct
answer is "Gonzales"!

209
00:10:30,750 --> 00:10:31,875
[KYON]
Liar!

210
00:10:31,958 --> 00:10:33,833
[HARUHI] Next up we
have Truck versus Kyon.

211
00:10:33,916 --> 00:10:35,125
--Who do you think will win?
--[MIKURU laughs]

212
00:10:35,208 --> 00:10:36,375
[KYON]
I'm not doing that!

213
00:10:36,458 --> 00:10:38,250
[HARUHI]
It's a tiny little pickup truck.

214
00:10:38,333 --> 00:10:39,875
Here're some fireworks.

215
00:10:39,958 --> 00:10:41,333
[KYON]
What? Why?

216
00:10:41,416 --> 00:10:43,750
I don't care how small
it is! I'm not doing it.

217
00:10:43,833 --> 00:10:45,458
Wait. You lit the fuses!

218
00:10:45,541 --> 00:10:47,875
-[engine revs]
-Dear god, I'm a human sparkler!

219
00:10:47,958 --> 00:10:50,166
Wha-What's that?
The truck's here!

220
00:10:50,250 --> 00:10:52,458
[KYON screams]

221
00:10:52,541 --> 00:10:54,416
[KYON] I don't want
to die like this!

222
00:10:54,500 --> 00:10:55,666
[explosion]

223
00:10:58,791 --> 00:11:02,208
Farewell. You will live in
our hearts forever, Kyon.

224
00:11:02,291 --> 00:11:03,541
[KYON]
I'm not quite dead.

225
00:11:03,625 --> 00:11:06,291
Whoa. You're still alive?
You're pretty tough.

226
00:11:06,375 --> 00:11:07,791
[KYON]
I was revived.

227
00:11:07,875 --> 00:11:09,458
After the fireworks exploded I--

228
00:11:09,541 --> 00:11:10,500
[bell dings]

229
00:11:14,291 --> 00:11:17,083
Yuki, your timing
still needs work.

230
00:11:38,458 --> 00:11:39,916
[HARUHI]
Here we g--!

231
00:11:40,000 --> 00:11:40,958
[HARUHI groaning]

232
00:11:49,958 --> 00:11:51,791
Miss Nagato,
I brought your tea--

233
00:11:51,875 --> 00:11:53,083
[screams]

234
00:11:53,166 --> 00:11:54,750
--Oh, Kyon!
--What's wrong?

235
00:11:54,833 --> 00:11:57,125
Miss Nagato... I just
saw her and she's...

236
00:11:57,208 --> 00:11:58,166
[KYON]
What about Nagato?

237
00:11:58,250 --> 00:12:00,833
Well, uh, it's just...
She's uh...

238
00:12:00,916 --> 00:12:02,208
Never mind.

239
00:12:02,291 --> 00:12:03,250
[KYON]
Hm?

240
00:12:05,666 --> 00:12:06,625
[knock]

241
00:12:31,500 --> 00:12:33,166
Hang in there, guys.

242
00:12:37,666 --> 00:12:38,916
[HARUHI]
Uh?

243
00:12:41,750 --> 00:12:43,125
[HARUHI]
Huh?

244
00:12:45,541 --> 00:12:46,666
[HARUHI]
Huh?!

245
00:12:46,750 --> 00:12:49,500
Hey, Kyon, does Yuki
have any sisters?

246
00:12:49,583 --> 00:12:51,000
[KYON]
Huh?

247
00:12:51,083 --> 00:12:59,166
[MIKURU humming]

248
00:12:59,250 --> 00:13:00,583
[MIKURU]
Hm?

249
00:13:00,666 --> 00:13:03,458
I've never seen these before!
Whose are they?!

250
00:13:05,041 --> 00:13:07,333
Oh, I haven't seen you
reading a book in forever.

251
00:13:07,416 --> 00:13:09,208
I always thought you were
more of a bookworm than--

252
00:13:09,291 --> 00:13:11,625
Whoa! A strategy guide?!

253
00:13:11,708 --> 00:13:13,541
You don't really use
those things, do you?

254
00:13:13,625 --> 00:13:15,875
I mean, if you really wanted
to beat a game that bad,

255
00:13:15,958 --> 00:13:17,583
couldn't you just hack into it?

256
00:13:17,666 --> 00:13:19,583
But that would be
considered cheating.

257
00:13:19,666 --> 00:13:21,666
[KYON]
Oh, right. Sorry...

258
00:13:21,750 --> 00:13:25,416
Hm? Do you want me
play that with you?

259
00:13:25,500 --> 00:13:28,000
Sure. I can play one round.

260
00:13:28,083 --> 00:13:29,500
A fighting game, huh?

261
00:13:29,583 --> 00:13:32,166
[NAGATO] Select character
and difficulty level.

262
00:13:32,250 --> 00:13:36,250
Hang on. Difficulty level?
Who am I setting that for?

263
00:13:36,333 --> 00:13:37,458
For me.

264
00:13:37,541 --> 00:13:39,916
[KYON] Whoa. She's been
playing this a lot.

265
00:13:41,375 --> 00:13:42,833
[ASAKURA laughs]

266
00:13:42,916 --> 00:13:46,125
[ASAKURA] Poor Miss Nagato.
She has no clue that I've made

267
00:13:46,208 --> 00:13:48,750
a back-up copy of myself.

268
00:13:48,833 --> 00:13:51,000
Ryoko Achakura has returned!

269
00:13:55,291 --> 00:13:56,250
[ASAKURA sighs]

270
00:13:57,791 --> 00:14:01,291
This isn't good... What in
the world could've gone wrong?

271
00:14:01,375 --> 00:14:02,750
[gasps]

272
00:14:02,833 --> 00:14:05,541
Miss Nagato! You knew I'd
return someday, didn't you?

273
00:14:08,375 --> 00:14:11,791
Let me out! Let me out!

274
00:14:11,875 --> 00:14:12,833
Huh?

275
00:14:14,791 --> 00:14:17,791
Ha! Now that I'm free,
prepare for your doom!

276
00:14:17,875 --> 00:14:20,166
As soon as I return
to my normal size,

277
00:14:20,250 --> 00:14:22,583
I will put an end
to you and him--

278
00:14:22,666 --> 00:14:24,125
Save me, please!

279
00:14:24,208 --> 00:14:25,000
[ASAKURA yelps]

280
00:14:25,083 --> 00:14:29,333
[ASAKURA panting]

281
00:14:29,416 --> 00:14:30,375
[gasps]

282
00:14:31,833 --> 00:14:34,208
[ASAKURA]
Miss Nagato... you saved m--

283
00:14:35,208 --> 00:14:38,166
[ASAKURA]
Let me out! Let me out!

284
00:14:40,500 --> 00:14:42,083
[ASAKURA]
Let me get this straight.

285
00:14:42,166 --> 00:14:44,250
You want me to move in with you?

286
00:14:44,333 --> 00:14:47,083
[NAGATO] Yes. It will be
easier to observe you.

287
00:14:47,166 --> 00:14:48,541
[ASAKURA]
I see...

288
00:14:51,166 --> 00:14:52,833
[ASAKURA grunts]

289
00:14:52,916 --> 00:14:55,250
[ASAKURA]
Uh, do you have another chair?

290
00:14:55,333 --> 00:14:56,333
I do not.

291
00:14:56,416 --> 00:14:57,916
You have to have something else!

292
00:14:58,000 --> 00:15:00,208
Stack two cushions
together or something!

293
00:15:00,291 --> 00:15:02,750
I only have two cushions,
including mine.

294
00:15:02,833 --> 00:15:06,625
I'll take it! I'll fold that
one in half and sit on it!

295
00:15:06,708 --> 00:15:07,666
[ASAKURA sighs]

296
00:15:09,500 --> 00:15:11,666
[NAGATO]
I will prepare dinner for us.

297
00:15:15,708 --> 00:15:16,625
[squeaking]

298
00:15:16,708 --> 00:15:18,250
[ASAKURA yelps]

299
00:15:18,333 --> 00:15:21,125
Oh, you decided
to use the chair.

300
00:15:21,208 --> 00:15:22,791
[ASAKURA]
Let's not talk about it.

301
00:15:22,875 --> 00:15:23,625
[YUKI]
Here you are.

302
00:15:23,708 --> 00:15:30,208
[ASAKURA gasping]

303
00:15:30,291 --> 00:15:31,041
I was joking.

304
00:15:31,125 --> 00:15:32,791
[ASAKURA]
Huh?! Really?

305
00:15:32,875 --> 00:15:34,458
Was it not obvious?

306
00:15:34,541 --> 00:15:36,500
[ASAKURA] Well, you did
bring me here in a bag.

307
00:15:36,583 --> 00:15:38,083
Considering my
current situation,

308
00:15:38,166 --> 00:15:40,500
I assumed that's how you
were going to treat me.

309
00:15:40,583 --> 00:15:43,333
I see. I will correct that.

310
00:15:43,416 --> 00:15:44,083
[ASAKURA grunts]

311
00:15:44,166 --> 00:15:45,000
[NAGATO]
Here you are.

312
00:15:45,083 --> 00:15:47,250
[ASAKURA yelps]
Change the bowl!

313
00:15:47,333 --> 00:15:48,291
[YUKI]
Oh.

314
00:16:08,708 --> 00:16:10,166
[HARUHI]
Here we g--!

315
00:16:10,250 --> 00:16:11,208
[HARUHI groaning]

316
00:16:16,166 --> 00:16:17,583
[COMPUTER CLUB LEADER]
Guess what?

317
00:16:17,666 --> 00:16:19,625
The computer club just made
this dodge ball video game,

318
00:16:19,708 --> 00:16:21,583
and we wanna challenge
you guys to a match.

319
00:16:21,666 --> 00:16:22,833
I decline!

320
00:16:24,583 --> 00:16:26,125
[ALL groaning]

321
00:16:27,041 --> 00:16:28,750
Man, I'm bored.

322
00:16:28,833 --> 00:16:30,833
[KYON]
Do you not see the irony here?

323
00:16:30,916 --> 00:16:33,666
[slurping]

324
00:16:33,750 --> 00:16:34,708
[HARUHI sighs]

325
00:16:34,791 --> 00:16:35,541
Speak.

326
00:16:35,625 --> 00:16:37,791
O... Kay.

327
00:16:37,875 --> 00:16:39,500
We just made this
dodge ball video game,

328
00:16:39,583 --> 00:16:41,416
and wanna challenge
you guys to a match.

329
00:16:41,500 --> 00:16:44,416
And if we win, you have to
give back all our computers!

330
00:16:44,500 --> 00:16:46,958
A game, huh? And?

331
00:16:47,041 --> 00:16:48,208
What?

332
00:16:48,291 --> 00:16:50,166
If we beat you guys,
what are we gonna get?

333
00:16:50,250 --> 00:16:51,750
Uh. Well, I...

334
00:16:51,833 --> 00:16:54,541
[HARUHI] Last time ya lost you
agreed to obey my every command.

335
00:16:54,625 --> 00:16:57,125
You don't have much to bet,
except your lives.

336
00:16:57,208 --> 00:16:58,208
Our lives?!

337
00:16:58,291 --> 00:17:01,041
Well, make me an offer.

338
00:17:01,125 --> 00:17:03,416
Fine. We'll bet this.

339
00:17:03,500 --> 00:17:04,208
[MIKURU screams]

340
00:17:04,291 --> 00:17:05,125
[KOIZUMI laughs]

341
00:17:05,208 --> 00:17:06,208
[KYON]
The price tag's on it!

342
00:17:06,291 --> 00:17:08,291
It is composed of
30% chicken bones,

343
00:17:08,375 --> 00:17:12,041
40% monkey bones,
and 30% turtle bones.

344
00:17:12,125 --> 00:17:14,583
[HARUHI]
Ha, ha! Deal! Game on!

345
00:17:14,666 --> 00:17:16,458
[COMPUTER CLUB LEADER]
Uh. Really?!

346
00:17:16,541 --> 00:17:18,708
--[KYON] Yep. Figures.
--[HARUHI laughing]

347
00:17:18,791 --> 00:17:20,750
We'll give you a quick
tutorial on it and then--

348
00:17:20,833 --> 00:17:23,416
--[HARUHI yells]
--[COMPUTER CLUB LEADER sobs]

349
00:17:23,500 --> 00:17:25,333
I don't wanna play
your lame game.

350
00:17:25,416 --> 00:17:28,208
We're gonna go play
the real thing!

351
00:17:28,291 --> 00:17:29,583
[CLUB MEMBERS]
Uh...

352
00:17:29,666 --> 00:17:31,000
[KYON]
Sorry guys.

353
00:17:31,083 --> 00:17:33,458
[HARUHI]
Okay losers, it's show time!

354
00:17:33,541 --> 00:17:35,666
You guys ready to
meet your maker?

355
00:17:35,750 --> 00:17:37,875
Get ready, 'cause
this is gonna hurt!

356
00:17:37,958 --> 00:17:40,791
Try and catch this...
If you think you can!

357
00:17:40,875 --> 00:17:43,958
Go on, I dare ya!

358
00:17:44,041 --> 00:17:45,083
Incoming!

359
00:17:45,166 --> 00:17:46,666
[screams]

360
00:17:46,750 --> 00:17:47,708
Huh?!

361
00:17:50,000 --> 00:17:51,333
Are you okay?

362
00:17:51,416 --> 00:17:52,375
[BOTH gasp]

363
00:17:53,625 --> 00:17:55,291
I'm feeling so powerful now.

364
00:17:55,375 --> 00:17:56,666
Me too!

365
00:17:56,750 --> 00:17:57,958
Me three.

366
00:17:58,041 --> 00:17:59,708
What's with this aura?

367
00:17:59,791 --> 00:18:03,000
Haruhi Suzumiya has caused
a shift in this reality.

368
00:18:03,083 --> 00:18:04,291
The humans in the area

369
00:18:04,375 --> 00:18:07,750
have had their abilities
increased by 100%.

370
00:18:07,833 --> 00:18:09,541
We better be careful then.

371
00:18:09,625 --> 00:18:11,666
We might disintegrate
if we use full power.

372
00:18:11,750 --> 00:18:13,333
Wait! That can't be okay.

373
00:18:13,416 --> 00:18:16,333
I'm feelin' powerful vibes
comin' from over there.

374
00:18:16,416 --> 00:18:18,041
We're gonna stick
it to 'em, Kyon.

375
00:18:18,125 --> 00:18:20,166
Bad idea!

376
00:18:20,250 --> 00:18:22,750
[Kyon groaning]

377
00:18:22,833 --> 00:18:25,458
[KYON]
No way. I can see it coming.

378
00:18:25,541 --> 00:18:26,583
Nice, Kyon!

379
00:18:26,666 --> 00:18:27,708
[KYON]
Koizumi!

380
00:18:27,791 --> 00:18:29,625
[MEMBER A grunts]

381
00:18:29,708 --> 00:18:30,458
What the...?!

382
00:18:30,541 --> 00:18:31,208
[yells]

383
00:18:31,291 --> 00:18:31,875
[BOTH]
Huh?!

384
00:18:31,958 --> 00:18:32,416
[KYON]
Watch out!

385
00:18:32,500 --> 00:18:33,208
[BOTH gasp]

386
00:18:33,291 --> 00:18:34,416
[HARUHI grunts]

387
00:18:34,500 --> 00:18:37,333
Not bad! Let's see
how you dodge this one.

388
00:18:37,416 --> 00:18:39,791
[yelling]

389
00:18:39,875 --> 00:18:42,458
How long's this court
supposed to be, anyway?

390
00:18:42,541 --> 00:18:44,333
Take this!

391
00:18:48,375 --> 00:18:49,375
It's supersonic.

392
00:18:49,458 --> 00:18:50,375
We're all gonna die!

393
00:18:50,458 --> 00:18:51,250
Bring it!

394
00:18:51,333 --> 00:18:57,291
[COMPUTER CLUB LEADER grunting]

395
00:18:57,375 --> 00:18:58,333
[Both]
Uh?!

396
00:19:00,833 --> 00:19:02,791
[COMPUTER CLUB LEADER]
Heh, heh.

397
00:19:02,875 --> 00:19:06,000
Oh, yeah... I'm lovin' this.

398
00:19:06,083 --> 00:19:09,041
C'mon, guys! Are we crankin'
this up a notch or what?!

399
00:19:09,125 --> 00:19:10,291
Please don't.

400
00:19:10,375 --> 00:19:14,166
[MIKURU]
Uh... Huh?! Huh. Uh-oh.

401
00:19:16,833 --> 00:19:19,208
[KYON]
I knew it would end this way.

402
00:19:19,291 --> 00:19:21,583
[NAGATO] No one's come to
collect their corpses yet.

403
00:19:21,666 --> 00:19:23,208
[KYON]
That's 'cause they're not dead.

404
00:19:30,750 --> 00:19:32,583
[KYON]
But I don't want it...

405
00:19:52,791 --> 00:19:54,333
[HARUHI]
Here we g--!

406
00:19:54,416 --> 00:19:55,375
[HARUHI groaning]

407
00:20:01,375 --> 00:20:03,041
Hey, Kyon...

408
00:20:03,125 --> 00:20:04,833
[KYON]
Hm? What's the matter?

409
00:20:04,916 --> 00:20:06,958
I found a bunch of
clothes on the rack,

410
00:20:07,041 --> 00:20:09,958
and I can't figure out
who they belong to.

411
00:20:10,041 --> 00:20:12,333
Oh, those are
probably Nagato's.

412
00:20:12,416 --> 00:20:15,000
Seems like she's been getting
a lot of new outfits lately.

413
00:20:15,083 --> 00:20:18,625
Oh. Yeah, I guess
that makes sense then.

414
00:20:18,708 --> 00:20:20,208
[MIKURU]
I see how it is...

415
00:20:20,291 --> 00:20:22,791
[KYON] Is this the start of a
cosplay rivalry between them?!

416
00:20:22,875 --> 00:20:25,083
[MIKURU]
Kyon, I made you tea.

417
00:20:25,166 --> 00:20:27,500
[KYON]
Uh. Thank you very much.

418
00:20:27,583 --> 00:20:28,458
[MIKURU]
Huh?

419
00:20:28,541 --> 00:20:29,666
Here's some more tea, Kyon.

420
00:20:29,750 --> 00:20:30,875
[KYON]
Uh. Thanks?

421
00:20:32,375 --> 00:20:33,541
Have another cup, Kyon!

422
00:20:33,625 --> 00:20:35,375
[KYON]
Too much tea!

423
00:20:35,458 --> 00:20:38,583
What's going on? Are you
guys having a costume party?

424
00:20:38,666 --> 00:20:40,458
--[MIKURU wails]
--Who knows?

425
00:20:41,583 --> 00:20:42,250
[MIKURU]
Kyon?

426
00:20:42,333 --> 00:20:43,250
[KYON]
Hm?

427
00:20:43,333 --> 00:20:45,041
[MIKURU]
I can't take this anymore.

428
00:20:45,125 --> 00:20:46,708
[KYON]
Miss Asahina?!

429
00:20:46,791 --> 00:20:48,541
[MIKURU] Trying to
compete with Miss Nagato

430
00:20:48,625 --> 00:20:51,083
wasn't such a good
idea after all.

431
00:20:51,166 --> 00:20:52,541
I'm a total failure.

432
00:20:52,625 --> 00:20:54,541
[KYON]
Easy now. Don't laugh.

433
00:20:54,625 --> 00:20:56,458
Oh, come on. That's not true.

434
00:20:56,541 --> 00:20:59,541
You looked fantastic in
every costume you had on.

435
00:20:59,625 --> 00:21:01,166
Have a little confidence.

436
00:21:01,250 --> 00:21:01,708
[MIKURU]
Really?

437
00:21:01,791 --> 00:21:03,458
[KYON screams]

438
00:21:09,416 --> 00:21:11,500
[knocking, door opens]

439
00:21:11,583 --> 00:21:14,708
Hey there. What's up? Hm?

440
00:21:14,791 --> 00:21:16,791
That's cool. You beat the game.

441
00:21:16,875 --> 00:21:18,500
It moved me to tears.

442
00:21:18,583 --> 00:21:19,958
Yeah. I bet.

443
00:21:21,958 --> 00:21:25,166
I will let you borrow my copies
of the game, manga, and novels

444
00:21:25,250 --> 00:21:26,166
in the series.

445
00:21:26,250 --> 00:21:28,166
[KYON]
Gee. Thanks.

446
00:21:28,250 --> 00:21:29,625
Listen, I'm really flattered

447
00:21:29,708 --> 00:21:31,333
that you want to loan
these out to me,

448
00:21:31,416 --> 00:21:33,541
but you don't have to give
me everything all at once.

449
00:21:33,625 --> 00:21:34,875
It's not a problem.

450
00:21:34,958 --> 00:21:36,458
Those are my loaner copies.

451
00:21:36,541 --> 00:21:37,833
[KYON]
I've heard of this!

452
00:21:37,916 --> 00:21:40,375
One to store, one to display,
and one to loan out!

453
00:21:40,458 --> 00:21:43,041
Besides, I have this
to keep me busy for now.

454
00:21:43,125 --> 00:21:44,291
[KYON]
The sequel?!

455
00:21:44,375 --> 00:21:46,708
They are also making an
anime based on the game.

456
00:21:46,791 --> 00:21:48,916
[KYON] That's the most
excited I've ever seen her.

457
00:21:49,000 --> 00:21:53,041
Hey, Kyon. That looks heavy.
Would you like me to help you?

458
00:21:53,125 --> 00:21:54,750
[KYON]
Uh... No. I got it.

459
00:21:55,958 --> 00:21:57,916
Don't tell me you're
into maid moe!

460
00:21:58,000 --> 00:21:59,708
[KYON]
No! These are Nagato's.

461
00:21:59,791 --> 00:22:02,000
That's just sick! Get rid of it!

462
00:22:02,083 --> 00:22:04,291
[KYON] But these are
rated E for everyone!

463
00:22:08,166 --> 00:22:15,083
[ASAKURA grunting]

464
00:22:15,166 --> 00:22:17,625
[ASAKURI]
I can't reach any higher...

465
00:22:17,708 --> 00:22:20,291
I had a feeling
this was gonna happen.

466
00:22:20,375 --> 00:22:23,750
If only I have a stool
to stand on, or...

467
00:22:23,833 --> 00:22:25,875
Yeah! Something like that!

468
00:22:25,958 --> 00:22:26,791
That's not a stool!

469
00:22:26,875 --> 00:22:29,500
--That's a baby walker!
--Oh.

470
00:22:29,583 --> 00:22:31,250
[ASAKURA] It's not right
for you to always pick me up

471
00:22:31,333 --> 00:22:33,791
everytime I can't
reach something.

472
00:22:33,875 --> 00:22:36,708
I really should come up
with a different solution.

473
00:22:36,791 --> 00:22:40,250
If only I had my own chair
or stool or something.

474
00:22:40,333 --> 00:22:42,666
Yeah! Something like this.

475
00:22:42,750 --> 00:22:45,291
I am not a baby!

476
00:22:45,375 --> 00:22:47,750
[sighs] I guess this
will have to do.

477
00:22:47,833 --> 00:22:50,458
At least I won't be
dependent on Nagato anymore.

478
00:22:50,541 --> 00:22:52,750
I can move around on my own.

479
00:22:52,833 --> 00:22:54,166
Wait.

480
00:22:54,250 --> 00:22:56,125
My legs don't reach the ground!

481
00:22:56,208 --> 00:22:58,791
Stop laughing! It's not funny!

482
00:22:58,875 --> 00:23:03,375
Fine. I don't wanna be your
friend anymore, Miss Nagato.

483
00:23:03,458 --> 00:23:05,583
Hey, wait! What are you doing?

484
00:23:05,666 --> 00:23:07,000
We're playing merry-go-round.

485
00:23:07,083 --> 00:23:08,583
What for?!

486
00:23:08,666 --> 00:23:11,666
[ASAKURA] If she thinks this is
gonna cheer me up, she's wrong.

487
00:23:12,958 --> 00:23:15,333
[ASAKURA] It's not that I
don't like this kind of stuff.

488
00:23:15,416 --> 00:23:16,833
I mean, I do.

489
00:23:16,916 --> 00:23:18,791
Is this as fast as she can go?

490
00:23:18,875 --> 00:23:22,041
Anyway, I refuse to
have fun anym-- Ah!

491
00:23:22,125 --> 00:23:25,166
[ASAKURA laughing]

492
00:23:25,250 --> 00:23:27,125
[WOMAN ON TV]
You... saved me.

493
00:23:27,208 --> 00:23:28,958
But you're the Head Maid.

494
00:23:29,041 --> 00:23:30,958
Was that your stomach growling?

495
00:23:31,041 --> 00:23:33,041
If you're hungry,
you really should eat.

496
00:23:33,125 --> 00:23:34,958
Come on, I'll make
you something.

497
00:23:36,708 --> 00:23:39,708
[ASAKURA] I've been put in
a device for babies again!

498
00:23:45,208 --> 00:23:46,791
Enough!

499
00:23:46,875 --> 00:23:49,041
I let you carry me in this
thing because it was useful!

500
00:23:49,125 --> 00:23:51,250
But I want out of it right now!

501
00:23:51,333 --> 00:23:53,583
Where does a person go to
buy something like this?

502
00:23:53,666 --> 00:23:54,958
Does it even have a name?

503
00:23:55,041 --> 00:23:57,208
It's a child safety bag
for children, isn't it?

504
00:23:57,291 --> 00:23:58,458
It's a secret.

505
00:24:00,583 --> 00:24:02,375
[ASAKURA] Fine. If that's
how it's going to be,

506
00:24:02,458 --> 00:24:04,458
I won't cook
for you anymore.

507
00:24:04,541 --> 00:24:05,875
[ASAKURA]
Uh?

508
00:24:05,958 --> 00:24:08,875
Ah! What are you doing?
Why did you stand up like that?!

509
00:24:10,125 --> 00:24:11,250
♪ This is a paradise... ♪

510
00:24:11,333 --> 00:24:13,375
[ASAKURA]
Why is she singing?!

511
00:24:13,458 --> 00:24:16,250
As if singing a song is
gonna make it all better.

512
00:24:16,333 --> 00:24:18,625
♪ At the bottom
of a lonely heart. ♪

513
00:24:18,708 --> 00:24:21,958
[ASAKURA] I am definitely not
in the mood for this nonsense.

514
00:24:22,041 --> 00:24:25,000
The music is much too
upbeat for my taste.

515
00:24:25,083 --> 00:24:26,541
--[ASAKURA laughs]
--[NAGATO singing]

516
00:24:26,625 --> 00:24:30,958
This is so much fun!
I wanna sing next! Woo!

517
00:24:31,041 --> 00:24:33,666
[NAGATO]
♪ ...or is it all a dream? ♪

518
00:24:33,750 --> 00:24:36,583
♪ Trapped in these bonds. ♪

519
00:24:36,666 --> 00:24:39,500
♪ Together all the way. ♪

520
00:24:39,583 --> 00:24:42,541
♪ We can't let go. ♪

521
00:24:42,625 --> 00:24:45,291
♪ This our destiny. ♪

522
00:24:51,166 --> 00:24:52,666
[HARUHI]
Here we g--!

523
00:24:52,750 --> 00:24:53,708
[HARUHI groaning]

524
00:24:56,666 --> 00:24:58,083
Hey guys!

525
00:24:58,166 --> 00:25:00,000
Thanks for comin' out on this
beautiful day to take part

526
00:25:00,083 --> 00:25:02,708
in the SOS Brigade's
Lots of Girls Field Day!

527
00:25:02,791 --> 00:25:04,958
The weather's perfect!
So without further ado,

528
00:25:05,041 --> 00:25:06,041
let's have some fun!

529
00:25:06,125 --> 00:25:07,291
[applause]

530
00:25:07,375 --> 00:25:08,583
Hey, momma?

531
00:25:08,666 --> 00:25:10,750
What are all the
weird people doing?

532
00:25:10,833 --> 00:25:12,541
[MOTHER]
Shh. Don't stare at them.

533
00:25:12,625 --> 00:25:15,291
[HARUHI]
Hey Kyon, pay attention!

534
00:25:15,375 --> 00:25:18,333
We have to divide everyone
into teams before we start.

535
00:25:18,416 --> 00:25:20,750
There's a red and a white team,
so check your card.

536
00:25:20,833 --> 00:25:22,166
[KYON]
Red.

537
00:25:22,250 --> 00:25:24,416
Hey Suzumiya, my card's
different from everyone else's.

538
00:25:24,500 --> 00:25:25,500
What's up?

539
00:25:25,583 --> 00:25:26,916
[HARUHI]
Oh, yeah. That's the loser card.

540
00:25:27,000 --> 00:25:28,500
I'm a loser?!

541
00:25:28,583 --> 00:25:31,083
Ya have to do whatever it says
before you can draw another one.

542
00:25:31,166 --> 00:25:32,500
[TANIGUCHI]
Do I sing it here, or...?

543
00:25:32,583 --> 00:25:33,958
Find a corner somewhere.

544
00:25:34,041 --> 00:25:36,750
You're on the red team, huh?
I'm on the white team.

545
00:25:36,833 --> 00:25:38,083
Good for you, dude.

546
00:25:38,166 --> 00:25:40,583
You know, Miss Suzumiya's
on the white team, too.

547
00:25:40,666 --> 00:25:42,375
Isn't it strange how when
she has these drawings

548
00:25:42,458 --> 00:25:43,916
you never end up on her team?

549
00:25:44,000 --> 00:25:45,750
I guess I'm lucky like that.

550
00:25:45,833 --> 00:25:48,791
Now that everyone's on a team,
we'll start the first event.

551
00:25:48,875 --> 00:25:50,333
The scavenger hunt.

552
00:25:50,416 --> 00:25:53,291
I need one person from each team
to step up and pick a card.

553
00:25:53,375 --> 00:25:54,791
I'll go for white team!

554
00:25:54,875 --> 00:25:56,500
Watch your back out there, Kyon!

555
00:25:56,583 --> 00:25:57,708
Yeah, good luck!

556
00:25:57,791 --> 00:25:59,083
Huh? I don't wanna.

557
00:25:59,166 --> 00:26:01,666
All right, contestants.
Please draw your cards.

558
00:26:01,750 --> 00:26:03,000
Don't open 'em yet!

559
00:26:03,083 --> 00:26:04,875
Okay. When I say go.

560
00:26:04,958 --> 00:26:07,708
Ready, set, go!

561
00:26:07,791 --> 00:26:09,875
[KYON]
Uh?! That's not a thing!

562
00:26:09,958 --> 00:26:12,666
Oh, whatever...
Come on, Koizumi.

563
00:26:12,750 --> 00:26:14,083
Go!

564
00:26:14,166 --> 00:26:16,125
Let's have a look at your card
and see if you're right.

565
00:26:16,208 --> 00:26:17,416
[KYON]
Yeah...

566
00:26:17,500 --> 00:26:20,416
Ah! An emotional barrier.
Explain your choice.

567
00:26:20,500 --> 00:26:23,083
Okay, Koizumi.

568
00:26:23,166 --> 00:26:23,791
I love you.

569
00:26:23,875 --> 00:26:25,375
[KOIZUMI gasps]

570
00:26:25,458 --> 00:26:26,583
[HARUHI gasps]

571
00:26:26,666 --> 00:26:28,750
But I don't, so there's
a barrier here. See?

572
00:26:28,833 --> 00:26:31,875
Your attention!
Haruhi's passed out,

573
00:26:31,958 --> 00:26:34,000
so we're gonna
take a little break.

574
00:26:34,083 --> 00:26:35,791
I'm afraid I'll have to
leave for a little while

575
00:26:35,875 --> 00:26:38,750
and go deal with a rather large
closed space that just formed.

576
00:26:38,833 --> 00:26:40,333
Yeah. Sorry about that.

577
00:26:40,416 --> 00:26:42,875
Shouldn't we take Miss
Suzumiya to the hospital?

578
00:26:42,958 --> 00:26:44,416
Maybe she has a fever?

579
00:26:44,500 --> 00:26:46,791
No. I don't think
that's the problem.

580
00:26:46,875 --> 00:26:50,125
Haruhi Suzumiya managed
to hang onto her sanity.

581
00:26:50,208 --> 00:26:52,458
If her mind snapped,
it would've destroyed the world.

582
00:26:52,541 --> 00:26:53,625
Seriously?

583
00:26:53,708 --> 00:26:55,708
[TANIGUCHI sighs]
I finished singing it.

584
00:26:55,791 --> 00:26:58,333
[KYON]
Hm? Oh. Took you long enough.

585
00:26:58,416 --> 00:27:00,708
Hey! Whatever, give me a card.

586
00:27:00,791 --> 00:27:01,708
[KYON]
A what?

587
00:27:01,791 --> 00:27:03,250
Oh. Right. That.

588
00:27:03,333 --> 00:27:05,375
Go ahead, but I think
we're done now.

589
00:27:05,458 --> 00:27:06,625
[TANIGUCHI]
What are you talking about?

590
00:27:06,708 --> 00:27:07,750
You can't be done.

591
00:27:07,833 --> 00:27:08,791
[KYON]
Huh?

592
00:27:08,875 --> 00:27:09,958
[TANIGUCHI]
Hm...

593
00:27:10,041 --> 00:27:11,750
Another lousy card.

594
00:27:11,833 --> 00:27:13,708
What the heck? Now what do I do?

595
00:27:13,791 --> 00:27:15,375
I guess you're supposed
to bring one back here.

596
00:27:15,458 --> 00:27:16,875
Seriously?

597
00:27:16,958 --> 00:27:18,833
[HARUHI]
Sorry about that, everyone.

598
00:27:18,916 --> 00:27:20,916
I hope I didn't make
you worry too much.

599
00:27:21,000 --> 00:27:22,500
But, I'm feeling better now.

600
00:27:22,583 --> 00:27:25,250
I don't remember why I
passed out, but... Whatever.

601
00:27:25,333 --> 00:27:26,416
I'm good.

602
00:27:26,500 --> 00:27:28,750
Our next event is
gonna be tug-of-war.

603
00:27:28,833 --> 00:27:31,666
We did not bring a rope
with us. It was too heavy.

604
00:27:31,750 --> 00:27:33,416
Oh, that's okay!

605
00:27:33,500 --> 00:27:35,916
Since we don't have a rope,
we can use Kyon instead!

606
00:27:36,000 --> 00:27:37,208
Uhh!

607
00:27:37,291 --> 00:27:38,041
Umm, Haruhi?

608
00:27:38,125 --> 00:27:39,125
[HARUHI]
Yes, Kyon?

609
00:27:39,208 --> 00:27:40,500
You're not serious, are you?

610
00:27:40,583 --> 00:27:42,833
You're the only option
cause we don't have a rope.

611
00:27:42,916 --> 00:27:45,291
Koizumi disappeared,
so we can't use him.

612
00:27:45,375 --> 00:27:47,083
And it's way more fair this way!

613
00:27:47,166 --> 00:27:48,458
[KYON]
You look like you're having fun.

614
00:27:48,541 --> 00:27:49,291
[HARUHI]
Who, me?

615
00:27:49,375 --> 00:27:51,000
Never! [laughs]

616
00:27:51,083 --> 00:27:52,375
[KYON] You didn't
forget why you fainted!

617
00:27:52,458 --> 00:27:54,458
[HARUHI]
Ha, ha! Start tuggin'!

618
00:27:55,583 --> 00:27:57,500
A long time ago,
if two people wanted

619
00:27:57,583 --> 00:27:59,250
custody of the same child,

620
00:27:59,333 --> 00:28:01,833
they'd each grab hold of
the kid and start pulling.

621
00:28:01,916 --> 00:28:04,458
Whoever worried about the kid
being in pain would let go

622
00:28:04,541 --> 00:28:06,416
and got to be the parent.

623
00:28:06,500 --> 00:28:08,416
But I'm the kind of person
who gets what she wants,

624
00:28:08,500 --> 00:28:09,875
even if I have to break it!

625
00:28:09,958 --> 00:28:10,750
[KYON]
But you just said...

626
00:28:10,833 --> 00:28:12,625
You gotta be the same way, Yuki.

627
00:28:12,708 --> 00:28:15,208
[KYON]
I saw that Nagato! Don't do it!

628
00:28:15,291 --> 00:28:18,833
[HARUHI]
♪ See it bloom! See it bloom! ♪

629
00:28:18,916 --> 00:28:20,666
♪ See the bright
red tulip bloom! ♪

630
00:28:20,750 --> 00:28:22,583
[KYON]
You're scaring me!

631
00:28:22,666 --> 00:28:24,875
--What... are... you singing?!
--[HARUHI] ♪ It tore apart. ♪

632
00:28:24,958 --> 00:28:25,875
[NAGATO]
Tearing?

633
00:28:25,958 --> 00:28:26,875
[KYON]
Yeah! Almost.

634
00:28:26,958 --> 00:28:30,125
That's the end of the song!

635
00:28:30,208 --> 00:28:31,666
[KYON]
My clothes!

636
00:28:31,750 --> 00:28:33,750
They tore off...

637
00:28:33,833 --> 00:28:35,958
[KID]
Whoa!

638
00:28:36,041 --> 00:28:38,458
Kid, learn from my mistakes.

639
00:28:41,958 --> 00:28:43,458
[COMPUTER CLUB LEADER whimpers]
I-It broke out.

640
00:28:43,541 --> 00:28:45,291
The kappa's on the loose.

641
00:28:45,375 --> 00:28:47,666
[COMPUTER CLUB LEADER gasps]

642
00:28:47,750 --> 00:28:48,458
[TANIGUCHI grunts]

643
00:28:48,541 --> 00:28:50,666
Look, Suzumiya, I got it!

644
00:28:50,750 --> 00:28:53,500
Can I... Cross the
finish line now?

645
00:29:15,291 --> 00:29:16,833
[HARUHI]
Here we g--!

646
00:29:16,916 --> 00:29:17,916
[HARUHI groaning]

647
00:29:21,000 --> 00:29:23,125
[HARUHI] Listen up, guys!
It's time for us to start

648
00:29:23,208 --> 00:29:24,708
the SOS Brigade's Encounters

649
00:29:24,791 --> 00:29:27,416
with the Unexpected
Setsubun Festival!

650
00:29:27,500 --> 00:29:29,875
But first, everyone
needs to draw a stick.

651
00:29:29,958 --> 00:29:31,041
Why?

652
00:29:31,125 --> 00:29:32,916
[HARUHI] To decide who's
playing the demon.

653
00:29:33,000 --> 00:29:34,666
Crap! Me again.

654
00:29:34,750 --> 00:29:36,666
Okay! You have to put these on.

655
00:29:36,750 --> 00:29:38,083
[TANIGUCHI]
You're kidding!

656
00:29:38,166 --> 00:29:41,000
Perfect! You look like a real
demon from every angle!

657
00:29:41,083 --> 00:29:44,166
Even the cops are gonna want to
haul you in for questioning!

658
00:29:44,250 --> 00:29:47,333
[TANIGUCHI] Great. Now kids are
gonna cry when they see me.

659
00:29:47,416 --> 00:29:48,625
Yeah, thanks a lot.

660
00:29:48,708 --> 00:29:51,000
Okay Mr. Demon, have
a seat there, please.

661
00:29:51,083 --> 00:29:53,375
[TANIGUCHI] So I just
sit down and that's it?

662
00:29:53,458 --> 00:29:54,791
[HARUHI]
Here are some roasted soy beans.

663
00:29:54,875 --> 00:29:56,250
You can eat 'em if you want.

664
00:29:56,333 --> 00:29:57,958
[TANIGUCHI]
Oh... Thank you?

665
00:29:58,041 --> 00:29:59,916
[HARUHI]
Ha! Your lucky sushi roll!

666
00:30:00,000 --> 00:30:02,291
The lucky direction
is south-southeast.

667
00:30:02,375 --> 00:30:04,041
[TANIGUCHI]
You're too kind.

668
00:30:04,125 --> 00:30:05,291
You guys want some?

669
00:30:05,375 --> 00:30:06,833
[HARUHI]
Oh, no. Don't worry about us.

670
00:30:06,916 --> 00:30:09,083
We're gonna get out of your way
and go throw some beans.

671
00:30:09,166 --> 00:30:10,666
Make yourself at home, okay?

672
00:30:10,750 --> 00:30:12,708
-[door shuts]
-[TANIGUCHI] Everyone's leaving?

673
00:30:12,791 --> 00:30:15,166
Okay. Have... fun.

674
00:30:15,250 --> 00:30:17,583
Alone. So alone.

675
00:30:17,666 --> 00:30:20,500
Okay! Let's start throwing
some beans, you guys!

676
00:30:20,583 --> 00:30:21,916
But instead of the usual chant,

677
00:30:22,000 --> 00:30:23,625
we're gonna say
"bring on the luck!"

678
00:30:23,708 --> 00:30:24,500
[ALL]
Hmm?

679
00:30:24,583 --> 00:30:25,666
Let me explain.

680
00:30:25,750 --> 00:30:27,416
Ever since I read
"The Crying Red Demon,"

681
00:30:27,500 --> 00:30:29,166
I've decided to be nice to them.

682
00:30:29,250 --> 00:30:30,416
[ALL]
Oh, I get it.

683
00:30:30,500 --> 00:30:32,458
Come on, guys!
Let's throw beans!

684
00:30:32,541 --> 00:30:34,125
[ALL]
Bring on the luck!

685
00:30:34,208 --> 00:30:36,083
Bring on the luck!

686
00:30:36,166 --> 00:30:37,125
[HARUHI]
Eat it!

687
00:30:37,208 --> 00:30:38,583
[KYON]
It's freakin' huge!

688
00:30:38,666 --> 00:30:40,583
Ha, ha! Look at Kyon gobble it!

689
00:30:40,666 --> 00:30:42,666
Go for it, Kyon! Inhale it!

690
00:30:42,750 --> 00:30:43,416
[KYON groaning]

691
00:30:43,500 --> 00:30:45,083
[NAGATO munching]

692
00:30:45,166 --> 00:30:48,541
[distant chattering, laughing]

693
00:30:48,625 --> 00:30:51,416
[TANIGUCHI]
I guess... I'll eat some beans.

694
00:30:51,500 --> 00:30:56,458
[distant chattering, laughing]

695
00:31:02,166 --> 00:31:03,125
[TANIGUCHI belches]

696
00:31:10,458 --> 00:31:12,458
Looks like she's trying
to pick a fight with me.

697
00:31:12,541 --> 00:31:14,250
Well two can play at this game!

698
00:31:14,333 --> 00:31:16,833
Ahh! You can't fool me!

699
00:31:16,916 --> 00:31:17,583
Wait!

700
00:31:17,666 --> 00:31:20,041
Oh, she got me.

701
00:31:20,125 --> 00:31:21,958
Uh. You've beaten me again.

702
00:31:22,041 --> 00:31:24,916
Setting such an obvious trap
was a stroke of genius.

703
00:31:25,000 --> 00:31:28,625
My lapse in judgement has proven
to be my downfall yet again.

704
00:31:28,708 --> 00:31:30,583
You must have a reason for
going through all this trouble

705
00:31:30,666 --> 00:31:33,291
to trap me! Well? What is it?

706
00:31:33,375 --> 00:31:35,375
It's good you
catch on so quickly.

707
00:31:35,458 --> 00:31:38,000
I have something that
I would like you to wear.

708
00:31:38,083 --> 00:31:40,750
[ASAKURA] I'm your prisoner,
so I can't refuse your request.

709
00:31:40,833 --> 00:31:42,583
Whatever it is, I'll wear it.

710
00:31:42,666 --> 00:31:44,583
[YUKI]
Negations complete.

711
00:31:44,666 --> 00:31:47,250
I wouldn't call what just
happened a negotiation.

712
00:31:47,333 --> 00:31:49,500
I just hope the
outfit's cute, is all.

713
00:31:49,583 --> 00:31:52,666
Could you've picked
a heavier kimono?!

714
00:31:52,750 --> 00:31:56,166
Sorry about that. You can sit
here and relax for a while.

715
00:31:56,250 --> 00:31:58,583
Oh, thank you. That's better.

716
00:32:00,625 --> 00:32:01,583
[ASAKURA]
Hm...

717
00:32:03,125 --> 00:32:04,833
[ASAKURA]
Now I get it!

718
00:32:04,916 --> 00:32:08,166
I don't care how much dessert
you bribe me with, I'm through!

719
00:32:08,250 --> 00:32:11,458
Ahh! I don't believe it...

720
00:32:11,541 --> 00:32:13,125
This must be the
legendary "obi spinning"

721
00:32:13,208 --> 00:32:14,416
I've been hearing about!

722
00:32:14,500 --> 00:32:16,250
I won't let you
get away with this!

723
00:32:16,333 --> 00:32:18,208
[NAGATO] You know you want it.
You know want it...

724
00:32:18,291 --> 00:32:20,708
[ASAKURA]
Oh, my!

725
00:32:20,791 --> 00:32:25,416
[ASAKURA laughs]

726
00:32:45,541 --> 00:32:47,083
[HARUHI]
Here we g--!

727
00:32:47,166 --> 00:32:48,125
[HARUHI groaning]

728
00:32:51,416 --> 00:32:54,166
[HARUHI] The SOS Brigade is
going to make a melodrama.

729
00:32:54,250 --> 00:32:56,000
I just wanna shake
things up around here,

730
00:32:56,083 --> 00:32:57,458
cause it's startin'
to get boring.

731
00:32:57,541 --> 00:32:59,166
I mean, every time
we have a quiz,

732
00:32:59,250 --> 00:33:02,375
the same thing always happens.
Kyon ends up exploding.

733
00:33:02,458 --> 00:33:04,166
It's not like I want to explode!

734
00:33:04,250 --> 00:33:05,833
We're gonna go around
the room right now,

735
00:33:05,916 --> 00:33:08,791
and I want everyone to
give me an idea for a story.

736
00:33:08,875 --> 00:33:09,750
You first, Kyon.

737
00:33:09,833 --> 00:33:10,875
Wait! I... What?!

738
00:33:10,958 --> 00:33:12,333
You're not even listening.

739
00:33:12,416 --> 00:33:14,333
Okay. Um, here's an idea.

740
00:33:14,416 --> 00:33:16,458
It's typical, but could
have the main character

741
00:33:16,541 --> 00:33:19,208
dying from a disease
or something.

742
00:33:19,291 --> 00:33:20,916
[HARUHI]
Great idea! 

743
00:33:21,000 --> 00:33:22,541
[KYON]
Overreact, much?

744
00:33:22,625 --> 00:33:23,875
It's genius.

745
00:33:23,958 --> 00:33:26,250
A tragic hero staring
death straight in the eye.

746
00:33:26,333 --> 00:33:30,416
Brilliant. Yes. Good.
Good one, Kyon.

747
00:33:30,500 --> 00:33:33,166
[KYON] Oh, cut it out.
You're embarrassing me.

748
00:33:33,250 --> 00:33:36,458
Okay, Koizumi. Whatcha got?

749
00:33:36,541 --> 00:33:38,791
You think your idea
can top Kyon's?

750
00:33:38,875 --> 00:33:40,000
I'll give it a shot.

751
00:33:40,083 --> 00:33:41,791
How about a story with
a romantic triangle,

752
00:33:41,875 --> 00:33:44,041
like those ones you see
in daytime soap operas?

753
00:33:44,125 --> 00:33:45,125
[HARUHI screams]

754
00:33:45,208 --> 00:33:46,375
[HARUHI]
Stealing someone else's lover!

755
00:33:46,458 --> 00:33:49,166
Love then hate, then revenge!
It's perfect!

756
00:33:49,250 --> 00:33:51,333
You feeling all right?

757
00:33:51,416 --> 00:33:53,625
I'll be okay.
Just give me a second.

758
00:33:53,708 --> 00:33:55,583
My vision's a little
blurry, that's all.

759
00:33:55,666 --> 00:33:57,875
If your vision is blurry,
you're not okay.

760
00:33:57,958 --> 00:33:58,625
Otaku.

761
00:33:58,708 --> 00:33:59,166
[HARUHI]
Ah!

762
00:33:59,250 --> 00:34:00,166
Or maids.

763
00:34:00,250 --> 00:34:00,916
[HARUHI]
Ah!

764
00:34:01,000 --> 00:34:02,166
Supply and demand!

765
00:34:02,250 --> 00:34:04,083
We'll give the otaku
what they wanna see.

766
00:34:04,166 --> 00:34:05,625
Welcome home, Master!

767
00:34:05,708 --> 00:34:07,416
[KYON]
I'm totally lost now.

768
00:34:09,500 --> 00:34:10,916
[HARUHI] All right,
I came up with a story

769
00:34:11,000 --> 00:34:12,708
using all the ideas
we thought of.

770
00:34:12,791 --> 00:34:15,541
I want you guys to check it out
and tell me what you think.

771
00:34:15,625 --> 00:34:17,375
It's called "The Gift
of the Maid Part 2:

772
00:34:17,458 --> 00:34:20,916
The Battle for Stolen Love
With Only One Month to Live."

773
00:34:21,000 --> 00:34:23,041
[KYON] It sounds like
some cheesy game show.

774
00:34:23,125 --> 00:34:24,541
And why is it part two?

775
00:34:24,625 --> 00:34:27,291
The title pretty much gives
away all the kung fu action.

776
00:34:27,375 --> 00:34:29,750
No it doesn't! There's
nothing kung fu about it!

777
00:34:29,833 --> 00:34:32,250
Well, it is about stolen love.

778
00:34:32,333 --> 00:34:35,500
[KYON] Okay, then. Let's go
with that. Picturing it...

779
00:34:35,583 --> 00:34:38,416
[HARUHI] All the characters
in the story are maids!

780
00:34:38,500 --> 00:34:39,916
[KYON]
Us too?!

781
00:34:40,000 --> 00:34:42,250
Everyone in the story's a maid.
And they love maids, too.

782
00:34:42,333 --> 00:34:43,958
They get into crazy
fights to decide

783
00:34:44,041 --> 00:34:45,333
who loves maids the most.

784
00:34:45,416 --> 00:34:47,375
They could decide in a
more maid-ly manner...

785
00:34:47,458 --> 00:34:50,291
So at the end of the month,
all the characters die?

786
00:34:50,375 --> 00:34:52,625
If the fighting doesn't
kill 'em first. [chuckles]

787
00:34:52,708 --> 00:34:54,541
What are you saying?!
You should die.

788
00:34:54,625 --> 00:34:57,458
Okay. If the story's
about stolen love,

789
00:34:57,541 --> 00:35:00,791
then who's going to become
the hero couple at the end?

790
00:35:00,875 --> 00:35:03,458
Well the last two maids
standing, of course.

791
00:35:03,541 --> 00:35:05,375
The last two, huh?

792
00:35:05,458 --> 00:35:07,416
But the only characters
left at the end

793
00:35:07,500 --> 00:35:09,416
are Kyon's and Koizumi's.

794
00:35:09,500 --> 00:35:13,000
Uh-huh. 'Cause only guys can
survive a fight that brutal.

795
00:35:13,083 --> 00:35:14,166
[MIKURU]
Uh...

796
00:35:14,250 --> 00:35:15,208
[HARUHI]
Hm?

797
00:35:16,875 --> 00:35:19,166
You like that, huh, Mu-chan?

798
00:35:21,708 --> 00:35:22,916
According to this,

799
00:35:23,000 --> 00:35:25,083
the first battle's between
you and me, Nagato.

800
00:35:25,166 --> 00:35:26,375
So it seems.

801
00:35:26,458 --> 00:35:28,500
[KYON] "Scene one,
Nagato's Aerial Chop.

802
00:35:28,583 --> 00:35:30,833
It has to look authentic,
so I want you to really hit him.

803
00:35:30,916 --> 00:35:33,958
This attack will break Kyon's
bones in about 26 places.

804
00:35:34,041 --> 00:35:37,583
Then, Kyon uses his first-aid
power-up and becomes invincible.

805
00:35:37,666 --> 00:35:39,875
He wins, just barely."

806
00:35:39,958 --> 00:35:43,583
Hang on, you are gonna be
careful not to kill me, right?

807
00:35:43,666 --> 00:35:44,666
[NAGATO]
Chop.

808
00:35:44,750 --> 00:35:45,708
[KYON screams]

809
00:35:48,541 --> 00:35:51,541
[KYON]
I'm turning into light!

810
00:35:53,708 --> 00:35:56,500
And we still ended
with an explosion.

811
00:36:17,000 --> 00:36:18,416
[HARUHI]
Here we g--!

812
00:36:18,500 --> 00:36:19,458
[HARUHI groaning]

813
00:36:26,916 --> 00:36:28,000
[ASAKURA]
After I get up in the morning,

814
00:36:28,083 --> 00:36:30,541
I usually wake
Miss Nagato up, too.

815
00:36:30,625 --> 00:36:33,291
But it's Sunday today, so I
think I'm gonna let her sleep in

816
00:36:33,375 --> 00:36:34,708
a little while longer.

817
00:36:34,791 --> 00:36:37,000
It's too bright.

818
00:36:37,083 --> 00:36:38,541
Go to sleep!

819
00:36:38,625 --> 00:36:40,708
Whatever, I'll go wash my face.

820
00:36:42,500 --> 00:36:45,500
Oh, no! I can't
do this by myself!

821
00:36:45,583 --> 00:36:49,250
I kicked her pretty hard.
I doubt she'll be waking soon.

822
00:36:49,333 --> 00:36:51,500
There's only one way to do this.

823
00:36:51,583 --> 00:36:53,500
The wall-jumping technique!

824
00:36:55,166 --> 00:36:56,958
[ASAKURA grunting]

825
00:36:57,041 --> 00:36:58,958
Ahhh!

826
00:36:59,041 --> 00:37:01,250
[ASAKURA]
Oh...

827
00:37:01,333 --> 00:37:03,125
I'm feeling hungry.

828
00:37:05,041 --> 00:37:06,500
What happened to you?

829
00:37:06,583 --> 00:37:09,916
Oh. My face. Water...

830
00:37:10,000 --> 00:37:11,250
Understood.

831
00:37:11,333 --> 00:37:12,833
[screaming]

832
00:37:12,916 --> 00:37:13,833
What are you doing?!

833
00:37:13,916 --> 00:37:15,583
According to the
data you provided,

834
00:37:15,666 --> 00:37:18,750
I chose the option that was
the easiest for you to react to.

835
00:37:18,833 --> 00:37:20,125
[ASAKURA]
Don't make me react!

836
00:37:20,208 --> 00:37:21,041
[growling]

837
00:37:21,125 --> 00:37:23,833
Face the fury of my vengeance!

838
00:37:23,916 --> 00:37:24,916
Ah!

839
00:37:25,000 --> 00:37:26,166
[BOTH]
Uh...

840
00:37:27,458 --> 00:37:29,625
Yuki! 'Bout time you showed up!

841
00:37:29,708 --> 00:37:31,666
You're never late.
What happened to you?

842
00:37:31,750 --> 00:37:33,250
[NAGATO]
I was unconscious.

843
00:37:33,333 --> 00:37:36,583
You're kidding! What it
an enemy?! Are you okay?

844
00:37:36,666 --> 00:37:37,791
[NAGATO]
Do not worry.

845
00:37:37,875 --> 00:37:40,833
It wasn't an enemy.
I am fine now.

846
00:37:40,916 --> 00:37:43,583
Everything's fine.
Everything's normal.

847
00:37:43,666 --> 00:37:45,125
[NAGATO]
You sure about that?

848
00:37:46,458 --> 00:37:49,541
[ASAKURA singing]

849
00:37:49,625 --> 00:37:51,125
[ASAKURA sighs]

850
00:37:51,208 --> 00:37:54,583
Rats. I guess Miss Nagato went
to go hang out with Kyon again.

851
00:37:54,666 --> 00:37:56,291
I shouldn't be cleaning
up around here!

852
00:37:56,375 --> 00:37:58,166
I'm one of the radicals!

853
00:37:58,250 --> 00:38:00,083
That does it. I'm going out!

854
00:38:02,416 --> 00:38:03,958
Not again!

855
00:38:04,041 --> 00:38:07,166
Oh, geez. Right, door.

856
00:38:09,000 --> 00:38:11,041
[ASAKURA]
Uh! Success! This is great.

857
00:38:11,125 --> 00:38:13,333
Umbrellas can reach
up really high.

858
00:38:13,416 --> 00:38:16,875
From now on, I'm gonna use
my umbrella for everything.

859
00:38:19,500 --> 00:38:21,000
[ASAKURA laughs]

860
00:38:21,083 --> 00:38:24,416
Nothing stands in the way of my
umbrella! Not even the elevator.

861
00:38:24,500 --> 00:38:25,666
Better watch out, Kyon.

862
00:38:25,750 --> 00:38:30,083
Because I'm coming up
to kill you! [chuckles]

863
00:38:37,958 --> 00:38:38,916
Meow.

864
00:38:42,375 --> 00:38:44,958
[ASAKURA] Children shouldn't
go out on their own.

865
00:38:45,041 --> 00:38:47,875
The world can be a dangerous
place sometimes.

866
00:39:08,041 --> 00:39:09,541
[HARUHI]
Here we g--!

867
00:39:09,625 --> 00:39:10,583
[HARUHI groaning]

868
00:39:13,833 --> 00:39:15,583
[door opens]

869
00:39:15,666 --> 00:39:16,541
[NAGATO]
I'm home.

870
00:39:16,625 --> 00:39:18,208
[ASAKURA]
Oh! Welcome back.

871
00:39:19,666 --> 00:39:21,208
[ASAKURA]
Huh?

872
00:39:21,291 --> 00:39:24,583
Ah! Please don't...

873
00:39:24,666 --> 00:39:27,916
Hey, Yuki! Thanks for
letting us come over today!

874
00:39:28,000 --> 00:39:29,166
[HARUHI]
Ahem!

875
00:39:29,250 --> 00:39:31,541
The SOS Brigade No Boys
Allowed Heart-Throbbing

876
00:39:31,625 --> 00:39:34,708
Valentine's Day Chocolate
Making Party is about to begin.

877
00:39:34,791 --> 00:39:36,541
[ALL]
Yay!

878
00:39:36,625 --> 00:39:39,166
Okay Mikuru. Hurry up
and take your clothes off.

879
00:39:39,250 --> 00:39:41,000
What for? A bath?

880
00:39:41,083 --> 00:39:42,750
I was thinking we could
make a life-size,

881
00:39:42,833 --> 00:39:44,166
Mikuru-shaped chocolate.

882
00:39:44,250 --> 00:39:46,291
No! I don't want to!

883
00:39:46,375 --> 00:39:49,166
Ha, ha, ha!
You know you want to.

884
00:39:49,250 --> 00:39:52,375
A large human shaped chocolate
would be unusually difficult

885
00:39:52,458 --> 00:39:54,041
to maintain and preserve.

886
00:39:54,125 --> 00:39:56,125
Oh, well. Whatever.
It was worth a shot.

887
00:39:56,208 --> 00:39:57,875
[MIKURU] You mean you guys
really would've done it

888
00:39:57,958 --> 00:39:59,625
if it were possible?

889
00:39:59,708 --> 00:40:01,041
[HARUHI]
I just realized something.

890
00:40:01,125 --> 00:40:03,125
We're gonna have lots
of left-over chocolate.

891
00:40:03,208 --> 00:40:04,875
[TSURUYA]
She's right!

892
00:40:04,958 --> 00:40:07,166
I know! We'll be able to
use up all the chocolate

893
00:40:07,250 --> 00:40:09,041
if we just make
whatever we want.

894
00:40:09,125 --> 00:40:11,750
Great idea! And we
can eat the mistakes.

895
00:40:13,833 --> 00:40:15,708
[MIKURU]
Is this arts and crafts?

896
00:40:17,333 --> 00:40:18,625
All done!

897
00:40:18,708 --> 00:40:21,458
Oh, I know this.
It's a Picasso, right?

898
00:40:21,541 --> 00:40:23,875
I didn't know you were
so artistic, Haru-nyan.

899
00:40:23,958 --> 00:40:25,000
It's Kyon's head.

900
00:40:25,083 --> 00:40:25,875
[BOTH]
Wha?!

901
00:40:25,958 --> 00:40:28,583
The likeness is 99.8% accurate.

902
00:40:28,666 --> 00:40:31,166
However, people who still
rely on vision to see

903
00:40:31,250 --> 00:40:33,291
will not be able to
tell the resemblance.

904
00:40:33,375 --> 00:40:37,041
[HARUHI] I can't tell whether
that was a compliment or not.

905
00:40:37,125 --> 00:40:38,583
[HARUHI]
Did you make a lion?

906
00:40:38,666 --> 00:40:40,208
Yes, this is Mu-chan.

907
00:40:40,291 --> 00:40:42,541
[HARUHI]
Wow! It looks great.

908
00:40:42,625 --> 00:40:44,000
And you made a crane.

909
00:40:44,083 --> 00:40:45,333
Uh-huh.

910
00:40:45,416 --> 00:40:47,583
[HARUHI] I could see these
hangin' out in a garden.

911
00:40:47,666 --> 00:40:50,416
Is yours all done, Yuki?

912
00:40:50,500 --> 00:40:51,416
[NAGATO]
Here.

913
00:40:51,500 --> 00:40:53,000
[HARUHI]
Are those chocolate bars?

914
00:40:53,083 --> 00:40:54,916
[TSURUYA] They look just like
they did before we melted them.

915
00:40:55,000 --> 00:40:57,625
[MIKURU] Wait. Didn't we
use up all of our ingredients?

916
00:40:57,708 --> 00:41:00,208
No way! She made these out
of that lump of chocolate.

917
00:41:00,291 --> 00:41:01,416
That's amazing!

918
00:41:01,500 --> 00:41:04,541
I know. It's amazing
how pointless they are.

919
00:41:04,625 --> 00:41:06,083
We still have a lot left over,

920
00:41:06,166 --> 00:41:09,583
so let's make a couple
batches of the usual things.

921
00:41:09,666 --> 00:41:12,875
I can totally handle putting
the powdered chocolate on.

922
00:41:12,958 --> 00:41:14,708
And I can wrap 'em all up!

923
00:41:14,791 --> 00:41:16,291
Stand back and watch
as I demonstrate

924
00:41:16,375 --> 00:41:19,125
the wrapping technique
of Tsuruya's Candy Store.

925
00:41:21,041 --> 00:41:22,333
What are you doing?!

926
00:41:22,416 --> 00:41:23,625
[sighs]

927
00:41:23,708 --> 00:41:25,208
[HARUHI]
I should be angry,

928
00:41:25,291 --> 00:41:28,041
but I'm blown away by how many
you munched before we noticed.

929
00:41:28,125 --> 00:41:29,666
[MIKURU]
That's amazing!

930
00:41:29,750 --> 00:41:31,541
[HARUHI]
Okay guys. Now what do we do?

931
00:41:31,625 --> 00:41:34,041
We're about to run
out of ingredients.

932
00:41:34,125 --> 00:41:35,541
Why don't we take
what we have left,

933
00:41:35,625 --> 00:41:37,666
and make two chocolate
cakes out of it?

934
00:41:37,750 --> 00:41:39,791
That's a good idea!
Let's do that.

935
00:41:39,875 --> 00:41:42,083
[HARUHI] They'll never
know we almost ran out.

936
00:41:42,166 --> 00:41:45,250
[TSURUYA] Use what ya got
till it's all gone, Haru-nyan.

937
00:41:45,333 --> 00:41:47,083
Huh?

938
00:41:47,166 --> 00:41:50,833
Thanks for having us over!
See you tomorrow!

939
00:41:50,916 --> 00:41:52,833
[door closes]

940
00:41:58,500 --> 00:42:00,125
[ASAKURA]
Have they all gone home?

941
00:42:00,208 --> 00:42:01,666
[NAGATO]
They have.

942
00:42:01,750 --> 00:42:03,708
I didn't know what was going on
when you put me in that box.

943
00:42:03,791 --> 00:42:06,250
I understand why you did it,
but I'm not happy about it.

944
00:42:06,333 --> 00:42:07,958
Not that I ever had a choice--

945
00:42:10,208 --> 00:42:11,958
--[ASAKURA screams]
--[NAGATO] Oh.

946
00:42:12,041 --> 00:42:15,000
What's going on?! Tell me why
there's a spring attached to me!

947
00:42:15,083 --> 00:42:16,875
I can't.

948
00:42:16,958 --> 00:42:19,416
You've been wanting to do this
to me since the beginning.

949
00:42:19,500 --> 00:42:21,000
Well I have news for you!

950
00:42:21,083 --> 00:42:24,375
I've been going easy on you
this... whole... time.

951
00:42:24,458 --> 00:42:26,958
What do you think I am?
A jack-in-the-box?!

952
00:42:27,041 --> 00:42:30,208
--[clonk]
--[groaning]

953
00:42:30,291 --> 00:42:33,750
[ASAKURA cries]

954
00:42:33,833 --> 00:42:36,708
[NAGATO]
Here. This is for you.

955
00:42:36,791 --> 00:42:38,750
[ASAKURA]
Huh? Uh!

956
00:42:38,833 --> 00:42:40,958
It's a piece of
the cake she made.

957
00:42:41,041 --> 00:42:42,958
[ASAKURA]
Hm...

958
00:42:43,041 --> 00:42:44,958
If she expects me to
forgive her shoddy treatment

959
00:42:45,041 --> 00:42:48,916
by accepting a piece of cake,
she's got another thing coming!

960
00:42:49,000 --> 00:42:51,458
I mean, I'm flattered she
even saved a piece for me.

961
00:42:51,541 --> 00:42:53,083
But there's no way
I'm going to be tempted

962
00:42:53,166 --> 00:42:54,833
by a measly little morsel of--

963
00:42:54,916 --> 00:42:58,166
[stomach growls]

964
00:42:58,250 --> 00:43:00,291
[ASAKURA]
Whatever. Just this once.

965
00:43:21,375 --> 00:43:22,875
[HARUHI]
Here we g--!

966
00:43:22,958 --> 00:43:23,916
[HARUHI groaning]

967
00:43:26,791 --> 00:43:28,875
[HARUHI]
Ahem! Attention!

968
00:43:28,958 --> 00:43:31,083
Since today is Valentine's Day,

969
00:43:31,166 --> 00:43:34,291
and since the SOS Brigade
observes all special occasions,

970
00:43:34,375 --> 00:43:36,166
we, the girls of the brigade,
had no choice

971
00:43:36,250 --> 00:43:38,041
but to make you boys
some chocolates.

972
00:43:38,125 --> 00:43:39,291
Oh, uh, thank you!

973
00:43:39,375 --> 00:43:40,875
Yes. Thank you very much.

974
00:43:40,958 --> 00:43:41,875
[HARUHI]
Stop!

975
00:43:41,958 --> 00:43:43,416
[KYON gasps]
Why can't I open it?

976
00:43:43,500 --> 00:43:45,125
We, the girls of
the SOS Brigade,

977
00:43:45,208 --> 00:43:47,458
think it's boring and archaic
in these modern times

978
00:43:47,541 --> 00:43:50,041
to just hand out chocolates
and go about our business.

979
00:43:50,125 --> 00:43:52,333
After all, we worked
hard to make those.

980
00:43:52,416 --> 00:43:54,416
Just because you're boys,
doesn't give you the right

981
00:43:54,500 --> 00:43:57,458
to eat those chocolates!
You have to earn 'em!

982
00:43:57,541 --> 00:43:58,916
[KYON]
What does she want?!

983
00:43:59,000 --> 00:44:00,208
[DEEP VOICE]
Too vague.

984
00:44:00,291 --> 00:44:02,291
I think I understand
your intention here.

985
00:44:02,375 --> 00:44:04,666
You want us to do something
for you that would make you

986
00:44:04,750 --> 00:44:07,333
want to give us the chocolates
in return, correct?

987
00:44:07,416 --> 00:44:09,500
Yeah. I guess that's
what I was goin' for.

988
00:44:09,583 --> 00:44:11,291
What do you mean?
Don't you know?

989
00:44:11,375 --> 00:44:13,666
Well? Do you have
any ideas for us?

990
00:44:13,750 --> 00:44:16,458
Yes, possibly. Sorry.
Give me a second here.

991
00:44:16,541 --> 00:44:19,333
I just have to fire off
this request for supplies.

992
00:44:19,416 --> 00:44:22,125
Anyway, we could always try
doing nothing for our something,

993
00:44:22,208 --> 00:44:25,125
and get the chocolates that way.
It's definitely worth a shot.

994
00:44:25,208 --> 00:44:26,541
Huh?

995
00:44:26,625 --> 00:44:28,958
[KOIZUMI] For example,
I've got a candy bar for you.

996
00:44:29,041 --> 00:44:30,083
Happy Valentine's Day!

997
00:44:30,166 --> 00:44:31,458
[KYON]
No thank you!

998
00:44:31,541 --> 00:44:34,375
Oh, that's too bad.
You didn't accept my valentine.

999
00:44:34,458 --> 00:44:35,583
But if you had taken it,

1000
00:44:35,666 --> 00:44:37,208
I would've been the
person giving something

1001
00:44:37,291 --> 00:44:39,250
instead of the one
getting something.

1002
00:44:39,333 --> 00:44:41,833
Therefore, you'd be obliged
to return the favor.

1003
00:44:41,916 --> 00:44:43,250
[KYON] Yeah, but,
if you apply that logic

1004
00:44:43,333 --> 00:44:44,833
to our situation with Haruhi,

1005
00:44:44,916 --> 00:44:47,541
you still have to do something
in order to get the chocolate.

1006
00:44:47,625 --> 00:44:48,625
[KOIZUMI]
You're so sharp.

1007
00:44:48,708 --> 00:44:50,000
[KYON]
Why you...

1008
00:44:50,083 --> 00:44:52,000
[KOIZUMI] I'm sorry.
I was just stalling for time.

1009
00:44:54,375 --> 00:44:56,791
Oh, would you mind
stepping back a bit?

1010
00:44:56,875 --> 00:44:58,250
Huh?

1011
00:44:58,333 --> 00:45:00,041
[KYON gasping]

1012
00:45:05,291 --> 00:45:07,458
Hello there. I'm just
an ordinary maid.

1013
00:45:07,541 --> 00:45:08,291
[KYON]
No way!

1014
00:45:08,375 --> 00:45:09,708
Here's what you asked for.

1015
00:45:09,791 --> 00:45:13,125
Thanks a lot for bringing it.
Mm-hm. It's all here.

1016
00:45:13,208 --> 00:45:14,625
[KYON]
Hm?

1017
00:45:14,708 --> 00:45:18,041
It's Mr. Arakawa. Oh, man.
What are these people up to now?

1018
00:45:18,125 --> 00:45:19,791
[KOIZUMI]
Let's get changed, shall we?

1019
00:45:19,875 --> 00:45:21,083
Uh? Okay.

1020
00:45:21,166 --> 00:45:23,291
Wait. Changed into what?

1021
00:45:23,375 --> 00:45:24,541
Why am I wearing this?

1022
00:45:24,625 --> 00:45:25,791
It's the male escort look.

1023
00:45:25,875 --> 00:45:27,125
Male escort?!

1024
00:45:27,208 --> 00:45:28,958
Well, it's the first thing
that popped into my mind

1025
00:45:29,041 --> 00:45:32,208
when I thought about someone
doing something for a woman.

1026
00:45:32,291 --> 00:45:33,791
I don't know about this.

1027
00:45:33,875 --> 00:45:36,416
What do you think, Miss Mori?
Do we look like male escorts?

1028
00:45:36,500 --> 00:45:38,750
The suits are perfect,
but you still need to have that

1029
00:45:38,833 --> 00:45:40,958
male escort smile
to complete the look.

1030
00:45:41,041 --> 00:45:42,375
The what?

1031
00:45:42,458 --> 00:45:44,833
Male escorts seduce women
with their killer smiles.

1032
00:45:44,916 --> 00:45:46,833
[KYON] But... I don't
want to kill anyone.

1033
00:45:46,916 --> 00:45:48,541
I have to be going now.

1034
00:45:49,500 --> 00:45:51,458
Seeing as to how we
don't have any other ideas

1035
00:45:51,541 --> 00:45:53,416
we might as well
give this one a try.

1036
00:45:53,500 --> 00:45:55,250
What the heck, right?

1037
00:45:55,333 --> 00:45:57,083
Okay. Here goes.

1038
00:45:58,375 --> 00:45:58,958
[ALL]
Huh?!

1039
00:45:59,041 --> 00:46:00,458
Wussup ladies?

1040
00:46:00,541 --> 00:46:03,000
I'm just ya average charmer
and the name's Kyon. Holla.

1041
00:46:03,083 --> 00:46:05,125
And I'm Itsuki,
the Crimson Super Ball.

1042
00:46:05,208 --> 00:46:07,291
Guess why they
call me that? Holla.

1043
00:46:11,000 --> 00:46:12,750
[screams]

1044
00:46:12,833 --> 00:46:14,250
What's wrong with you idiots?!

1045
00:46:14,333 --> 00:46:18,125
Get rid of those cheesy outfits!
You're making Mikuru cry!

1046
00:46:18,958 --> 00:46:21,875
[TSURUYA humming]

1047
00:46:24,458 --> 00:46:27,833
[TSURUYA]
This feeling... Who is that?

1048
00:46:49,458 --> 00:46:51,000
[HARUHI]
Here we g--!

1049
00:46:51,083 --> 00:46:52,166
[HARUHI groaning]

1050
00:46:57,625 --> 00:46:59,708
We better do somethin'
for Halloween.

1051
00:46:59,791 --> 00:47:01,625
It's not as simple
as going to Kyoto.

1052
00:47:01,708 --> 00:47:03,458
Do you know anything
about Halloween?

1053
00:47:03,541 --> 00:47:05,625
Like what it's about, and
what you're supposed to do?

1054
00:47:05,708 --> 00:47:07,041
Huh? Well, um...

1055
00:47:07,125 --> 00:47:09,791
I guess you need to
have pumpkins and bats?

1056
00:47:09,875 --> 00:47:12,916
Kyon's useless. What about
you, Koizumi. Do you know?

1057
00:47:13,000 --> 00:47:15,208
It would be far more
interesting if I pretended

1058
00:47:15,291 --> 00:47:18,125
not to know, so no.
I have absolutely no idea.

1059
00:47:18,208 --> 00:47:20,541
Oh, darnnit. I guess you're
in the dark like the rest of us.

1060
00:47:20,625 --> 00:47:21,833
Didn't you hear what he said?!

1061
00:47:21,916 --> 00:47:23,708
Whatever. We'll just
make it up as we go.

1062
00:47:23,791 --> 00:47:24,750
Hello!

1063
00:47:24,833 --> 00:47:26,250
Let's do a little research.

1064
00:47:26,333 --> 00:47:28,250
Yeah, but do you even
know where to start?

1065
00:47:28,333 --> 00:47:30,583
[HARUHI] For now, this is all
the information we've got.

1066
00:47:30,666 --> 00:47:33,000
[KYON] There are so many
things I could say right now...

1067
00:47:33,083 --> 00:47:34,916
Okay... Let's do this.

1068
00:47:35,000 --> 00:47:37,833
[BOTH]
Stare.

1069
00:47:37,916 --> 00:47:39,375
A-ha!

1070
00:47:39,458 --> 00:47:41,416
We need a guy wearing a cape
with a scary pumpkin on his head

1071
00:47:41,500 --> 00:47:42,375
and a bunch of bats!

1072
00:47:42,458 --> 00:47:43,750
I was thinking the same thing,

1073
00:47:43,833 --> 00:47:45,916
but there's gotta be
more to it than that.

1074
00:47:46,750 --> 00:47:48,500
--Look! We bought a pumpkin.
--[KYON panting] 

1075
00:47:48,583 --> 00:47:49,875
[KYON]
I bought it.

1076
00:47:49,958 --> 00:47:51,000
[HARUHI]
You ready?

1077
00:47:51,083 --> 00:47:51,541
[KYON]
Hm?

1078
00:47:51,625 --> 00:47:53,083
[HARUHI yells]

1079
00:47:53,166 --> 00:47:55,875
Ah! What are you doing?!

1080
00:47:55,958 --> 00:47:57,416
Carving a pumpkin's
a lot of work,

1081
00:47:57,500 --> 00:47:59,416
so I thought we could just
press it against your face

1082
00:47:59,500 --> 00:48:00,958
and make it--

1083
00:48:01,041 --> 00:48:03,083
What are you crazy?! Do you know
how hard those things are?!

1084
00:48:03,166 --> 00:48:05,291
[HARUHI] Mikuru, your job
is to carve out a face.

1085
00:48:05,375 --> 00:48:06,375
Okay!

1086
00:48:06,458 --> 00:48:07,666
[HARUHI]
And Yuki, you give her a hand.

1087
00:48:07,750 --> 00:48:08,666
Understood.

1088
00:48:08,750 --> 00:48:09,875
[HARUHI]
I'm gonna go out for a bit

1089
00:48:09,958 --> 00:48:11,958
and pick up the rest
of the things we need.

1090
00:48:14,333 --> 00:48:16,583
I finished carving the face.
What do you think?

1091
00:48:16,666 --> 00:48:19,208
The right eye is three
millimeters larger.

1092
00:48:19,291 --> 00:48:20,250
Ah...

1093
00:48:21,625 --> 00:48:24,083
The left eye is one
millimeter larger now.

1094
00:48:24,166 --> 00:48:25,416
Ah...

1095
00:48:25,875 --> 00:48:29,208
The mouth is 1.5 millimeters
smaller on the right.

1096
00:48:29,291 --> 00:48:32,291
The right eye is
.3 millimeters larger.

1097
00:48:34,708 --> 00:48:36,125
[MIKURU]
Sniff.

1098
00:48:36,708 --> 00:48:38,333
I have returned!

1099
00:48:38,416 --> 00:48:40,583
I got pretty much
everything we need.

1100
00:48:40,666 --> 00:48:42,958
Except the bats.
I couldn't find those.

1101
00:48:43,041 --> 00:48:44,166
What's up, Haru-nyan?

1102
00:48:44,250 --> 00:48:45,416
If you want bats,

1103
00:48:45,500 --> 00:48:46,833
the cave behind my
house has a bunch of 'em.

1104
00:48:46,916 --> 00:48:48,416
No way! Really?!

1105
00:48:48,500 --> 00:48:50,416
[KYON] Where the heck did she
find that horrible thing?

1106
00:48:50,500 --> 00:48:51,833
[KOIZUMI]
I have no idea...

1107
00:48:51,916 --> 00:48:53,666
Perhaps she's planning
on putting the pumpkin

1108
00:48:53,750 --> 00:48:55,250
and the cape on it.

1109
00:48:55,333 --> 00:48:56,291
[KYON]
You're kidding.

1110
00:48:57,875 --> 00:49:00,458
[KOIZUMI] He's looking quite
sinister now, don't you think?

1111
00:49:00,541 --> 00:49:02,958
It's like a shrine
to some pagan god.

1112
00:49:03,041 --> 00:49:04,458
Now I get it!

1113
00:49:04,541 --> 00:49:06,750
If I knew you guys were
getting ready for Halloween,

1114
00:49:06,833 --> 00:49:08,125
I would've brought some candy.

1115
00:49:08,208 --> 00:49:09,166
Candy?

1116
00:49:09,250 --> 00:49:11,083
That's what
Halloween's all about!

1117
00:49:11,166 --> 00:49:13,541
Kids dress up in monster
costumes, go door-to-door,

1118
00:49:13,625 --> 00:49:14,708
and you give them candy.

1119
00:49:14,791 --> 00:49:17,333
Really?! So that's
what it's all about?

1120
00:49:17,416 --> 00:49:20,000
My bad. I was going with the
idea that we had to make up

1121
00:49:20,083 --> 00:49:22,291
an original god to worship
and give offerings to.

1122
00:49:22,375 --> 00:49:23,583
You're kidding?!

1123
00:49:23,666 --> 00:49:26,291
Oh, well. Let's offer
up some candy to it.

1124
00:49:26,375 --> 00:49:27,875
Mikuru, do you have any candy?

1125
00:49:27,958 --> 00:49:31,916
Huh?! Uh... Uh. Uh!

1126
00:49:32,000 --> 00:49:34,375
This is all I had in my pocket.

1127
00:49:34,458 --> 00:49:36,083
[HARUHI] I don't know if it
really counts as candy,

1128
00:49:36,166 --> 00:49:37,375
but, whatever.

1129
00:49:37,458 --> 00:49:38,875
Perfect!

1130
00:49:38,958 --> 00:49:40,250
[KOIZUMI]
Trick, or treat?

1131
00:49:40,333 --> 00:49:42,208
[KYON]
Search and destroy.

1132
00:49:42,291 --> 00:49:43,458
We're done with it,

1133
00:49:43,541 --> 00:49:45,333
so let's ditch this guy
in the Computer Club.

1134
00:49:48,416 --> 00:49:49,291
[NAGATO]
I'm home.

1135
00:49:49,375 --> 00:49:50,791
[ASAKURA]
Welcome back.

1136
00:49:50,875 --> 00:49:53,625
I know you just came home,
but could we go to the market?

1137
00:49:53,708 --> 00:49:55,958
We don't have
anything for dinner.

1138
00:49:57,416 --> 00:49:59,291
Oh, how I love it when
you put me in the bag.

1139
00:49:59,375 --> 00:50:01,000
It's so warm and cozy.

1140
00:50:01,083 --> 00:50:02,541
Don't put me in it!

1141
00:50:02,625 --> 00:50:06,083
But if I run into that cat
again, I'll be unprotected.

1142
00:50:06,166 --> 00:50:08,000
[ASAKURA groans]

1143
00:50:09,458 --> 00:50:10,333
Here we are.

1144
00:50:10,416 --> 00:50:12,250
We are, at that.

1145
00:50:12,333 --> 00:50:15,333
Was there anything in particular
you wanted to have for dinner?

1146
00:50:15,416 --> 00:50:18,208
I would like to have
rabbit roti with a renegade

1147
00:50:18,291 --> 00:50:20,625
in a sherry glaze,
and a carrot puree.

1148
00:50:20,708 --> 00:50:23,208
[ASAKURA] Oh, look. Potatoes
and carrots are cheap today!

1149
00:50:23,291 --> 00:50:24,708
We could have curry.

1150
00:50:24,791 --> 00:50:26,125
Five steps to the right!

1151
00:50:26,208 --> 00:50:27,666
Fifty centimeters straight up!

1152
00:50:27,750 --> 00:50:28,958
Steady now!

1153
00:50:29,041 --> 00:50:31,291
Release the ingredients!

1154
00:50:32,333 --> 00:50:35,291
Bon appetit. Dinner is served.

1155
00:50:35,375 --> 00:50:41,083
[yawns]

1156
00:50:41,166 --> 00:50:44,333
[ASAKURA] Now that I'm teeny
tiny, I can't stay up late.

1157
00:50:45,583 --> 00:50:47,333
You've got school
tomorrow, Miss Nagato.

1158
00:50:47,416 --> 00:50:49,875
You should get to bed soon,
or you'll be too...

1159
00:50:51,791 --> 00:50:53,583
Go to sleep!

1160
00:51:14,791 --> 00:51:16,375
[HARUHI]
Here we g--!

1161
00:51:16,458 --> 00:51:17,416
[HARUHI groaning]

1162
00:51:29,333 --> 00:51:30,333
Hey Kyon, over here!

1163
00:51:30,416 --> 00:51:30,958
[KYON]
Hm?

1164
00:51:31,041 --> 00:51:32,500
Heads up!

1165
00:51:32,583 --> 00:51:34,333
What the heck are you doing?

1166
00:51:35,333 --> 00:51:36,791
Ahh!

1167
00:51:36,875 --> 00:51:37,833
Huh?

1168
00:51:38,708 --> 00:51:40,083
Hey! Don't you know
how scary it is

1169
00:51:40,166 --> 00:51:42,041
to have a balloon popped
that close to your face?!

1170
00:51:42,125 --> 00:51:43,541
Whoa! A main character

1171
00:51:43,625 --> 00:51:45,791
shouldn't make scary
faces like that, Kyon.

1172
00:51:45,875 --> 00:51:47,083
Here, take it.

1173
00:51:47,166 --> 00:51:49,375
You can try it on me,
if you want.

1174
00:51:49,458 --> 00:51:51,041
I'll hold the balloon this time.

1175
00:51:51,125 --> 00:51:52,958
You know, blow-guns
are pretty fun,

1176
00:51:53,041 --> 00:51:55,166
and they're super easy to use.

1177
00:51:55,250 --> 00:51:56,625
A-ha! That hurt!

1178
00:51:56,708 --> 00:51:58,625
You got me between
the nose and lip!

1179
00:51:58,708 --> 00:52:01,416
Gee. Sorry about that.
I guess it slipped.

1180
00:52:01,500 --> 00:52:03,958
[HARUHI]
You've got some nerve, Kyon.

1181
00:52:04,041 --> 00:52:06,000
That's a declaration of war!

1182
00:52:06,083 --> 00:52:07,291
[KYON laughing]

1183
00:52:07,375 --> 00:52:09,125
If you think I'm gonna
let you kick me around,

1184
00:52:09,208 --> 00:52:10,416
you've another thing coming.

1185
00:52:10,500 --> 00:52:11,833
Prepare for some pain!

1186
00:52:11,916 --> 00:52:14,166
I'm gonna shoot darts
into every hole in your body!

1187
00:52:14,250 --> 00:52:16,208
[KYON] Keep it clean!
We've got kids watching!

1188
00:52:16,291 --> 00:52:17,000
[HARUHI]
Die!

1189
00:52:17,083 --> 00:52:17,875
[KYON]
Incoming!

1190
00:52:17,958 --> 00:52:19,125
[MIKURU grunts]

1191
00:52:20,000 --> 00:52:21,375
Are you all right, Miss Asahina?

1192
00:52:21,458 --> 00:52:23,416
[HARUHI]
I'm sorry, Mikuru.

1193
00:52:26,250 --> 00:52:29,458
I promise I'll never aim a
weapon at another person again.

1194
00:52:29,541 --> 00:52:31,416
I swear it on Mikuru's grave.

1195
00:52:31,500 --> 00:52:34,500
Miss Asahina taught all of
us a valuable lesson today,

1196
00:52:34,583 --> 00:52:36,375
but she paid the ultimate price.

1197
00:52:36,458 --> 00:52:38,750
Thank you, Mikuru. Farewell.

1198
00:52:38,833 --> 00:52:41,375
Um... Excuse me,
I'm still alive.

1199
00:52:41,458 --> 00:52:43,208
[HARUHI] What are we going
to do about our duel?

1200
00:52:43,291 --> 00:52:45,083
We can't just walk away from it.

1201
00:52:45,166 --> 00:52:46,333
We can't use the blow guns,

1202
00:52:46,416 --> 00:52:48,333
and we still have a
ton of balloons left.

1203
00:52:48,416 --> 00:52:49,583
[KYON]
Hm...

1204
00:52:49,666 --> 00:52:52,041
I know! We're gonna have
a balloon art contest.

1205
00:52:52,125 --> 00:52:54,791
We can decorate Mikuru's
grave with our creations!

1206
00:52:54,875 --> 00:52:56,166
Just what I was I thinking!

1207
00:52:56,250 --> 00:52:59,416
Excuse me, I haven't
died yet. I'm alive.

1208
00:52:59,500 --> 00:53:00,666
[KOIZUMI]
And just like that,

1209
00:53:00,750 --> 00:53:03,500
the Asahina Cup Balloon
Art Contest is underway.

1210
00:53:03,583 --> 00:53:04,916
Whoever makes the
best decorations

1211
00:53:05,000 --> 00:53:07,208
on Miss Asahina's grave wins.

1212
00:53:07,291 --> 00:53:09,791
Hello there, everyone.
I'm Red Balloon Koizumi,

1213
00:53:09,875 --> 00:53:12,750
and I'll be judging and
providing the commentary today.

1214
00:53:15,958 --> 00:53:19,583
Kyon, I always wanted to settle
things with you this way.

1215
00:53:19,666 --> 00:53:21,375
Yeah, right. Dream on, buddy!

1216
00:53:21,458 --> 00:53:24,708
I knew a day like this would
come around eventually.

1217
00:53:24,791 --> 00:53:26,875
You know I'm totally
kidding though, right?

1218
00:53:26,958 --> 00:53:30,416
Get ready, balloon
fighters... Go!

1219
00:53:33,208 --> 00:53:35,416
Hm? What's that?

1220
00:53:35,500 --> 00:53:37,541
It's, uh, lotus root.

1221
00:53:37,625 --> 00:53:40,166
How 'bout yours?
It looks the same as mine.

1222
00:53:40,250 --> 00:53:42,291
It's sort of a... chain mine.

1223
00:53:42,375 --> 00:53:44,625
[BOTH]
I don't know how to do this!

1224
00:53:44,708 --> 00:53:46,416
[HARUHI]
Whatever! We made them,

1225
00:53:46,500 --> 00:53:48,416
so we might as well
use them to decorate.

1226
00:53:48,500 --> 00:53:50,625
And Miss Suzumiya
just scored 10 points.

1227
00:53:50,708 --> 00:53:52,791
[KYON] What?! She gets
10 points for that?!

1228
00:53:55,458 --> 00:53:58,208
[KYON] Oh, well. We couldn't
really do anything creative.

1229
00:53:58,291 --> 00:54:00,750
We just blew up balloons
and put twists in them.

1230
00:54:00,833 --> 00:54:03,083
But we twisted and
blew the best we could.

1231
00:54:03,166 --> 00:54:04,666
Yeah. We did, didn't we?

1232
00:54:04,750 --> 00:54:07,708
And somewhere along the way we
stopped caring about the score.

1233
00:54:09,000 --> 00:54:10,958
[HARUHI] This is boring.
Let's do somethin' else.

1234
00:54:11,041 --> 00:54:11,625
[KYON]
Okay.

1235
00:54:11,708 --> 00:54:12,916
[MIKURU whines]

1236
00:54:15,208 --> 00:54:16,541
[HARUHI grunting]

1237
00:54:16,625 --> 00:54:17,833
Rats.

1238
00:54:17,916 --> 00:54:20,125
Sorry, Mikuru, but the
balloons are so tangled

1239
00:54:20,208 --> 00:54:21,083
I can't get 'em off.

1240
00:54:21,166 --> 00:54:22,250
Wha...?!

1241
00:54:22,333 --> 00:54:24,083
[HARUHI] Don't worry!
I'll just pop 'em

1242
00:54:24,166 --> 00:54:27,583
--and you'll be good to go!
--Hey, what's up Nagato?

1243
00:54:27,666 --> 00:54:28,750
These things.

1244
00:54:28,833 --> 00:54:30,333
Hm? Yeah.

1245
00:54:30,416 --> 00:54:32,625
We got a lot of balloons
left over, huh?

1246
00:54:32,708 --> 00:54:34,875
I wonder why Haruhi
bought so many.

1247
00:54:36,375 --> 00:54:39,000
[HARUHI] Sorry, Mikuru, but I'm
the kind of woman who always

1248
00:54:39,083 --> 00:54:40,250
gives in to her desires.

1249
00:54:40,333 --> 00:54:41,708
May I have them?

1250
00:54:41,791 --> 00:54:44,041
Yeah. Help yourself. You can
take as many as you want.

1251
00:54:44,125 --> 00:54:45,666
--Thank you very much.
--[balloons pop]

1252
00:54:45,750 --> 00:54:48,750
--[popping continues]
--[MIKURU yelping]

1253
00:55:08,791 --> 00:55:10,458
[HARUHI]
Here we g--!

1254
00:55:10,541 --> 00:55:11,750
[HARUHI groaning]

1255
00:55:20,083 --> 00:55:21,333
Oh!

1256
00:55:22,250 --> 00:55:22,916
Huh?

1257
00:55:23,000 --> 00:55:24,625
[laughing]

1258
00:55:24,708 --> 00:55:26,875
Balloons are such powerful
things, aren't they?!

1259
00:55:26,958 --> 00:55:28,291
[NAGATO]
I think not.

1260
00:55:28,375 --> 00:55:30,500
However, it is my
understanding that one

1261
00:55:30,583 --> 00:55:33,625
can create the likeness of both
animals and plants from them.

1262
00:55:33,708 --> 00:55:36,083
[ASAKURA] Seriously?!
Balloons are awesome.

1263
00:55:36,166 --> 00:55:38,875
They might be the predecessors
of artificial life.

1264
00:55:38,958 --> 00:55:41,250
It's a form of humanoid
transmutation!

1265
00:55:41,333 --> 00:55:44,291
I will now attempt to
create the likeness of a dog.

1266
00:55:44,375 --> 00:55:45,666
Huh?

1267
00:55:45,750 --> 00:55:49,333
Ah! Miss Nagato!
It's scary! Stop it!

1268
00:55:49,416 --> 00:55:50,708
[NAGATO]
I'm done.

1269
00:55:50,791 --> 00:55:53,458
The air inside has conformed
to the shape of a dog.

1270
00:55:53,541 --> 00:55:55,041
It's cute. I'll give you that.

1271
00:55:55,125 --> 00:55:58,625
But watching it transform has
left me with emotional scars.

1272
00:55:58,708 --> 00:55:59,750
[exhales]

1273
00:56:01,625 --> 00:56:03,583
[ASAKURA]
Hm. It would be wonderful

1274
00:56:03,666 --> 00:56:06,458
if this could move
around on its own.

1275
00:56:06,541 --> 00:56:07,375
Understood.

1276
00:56:07,458 --> 00:56:09,208
No! Stop it!

1277
00:56:09,291 --> 00:56:10,708
[BALLOON DOG pants]

1278
00:56:10,791 --> 00:56:12,708
[NAGATO]
I was able to make it move.

1279
00:56:12,791 --> 00:56:15,291
Aw! So cute.

1280
00:56:15,375 --> 00:56:19,958
Ah! Come back! [giggles]

1281
00:56:20,958 --> 00:56:23,583
Fooled again!

1282
00:56:24,500 --> 00:56:27,000
Okay, you win. I thought
I could be happy,

1283
00:56:27,083 --> 00:56:29,500
and just play with the balloon
dog without having to worry

1284
00:56:29,583 --> 00:56:31,583
about falling into
one of your traps.

1285
00:56:31,666 --> 00:56:32,875
You should know better.

1286
00:56:32,958 --> 00:56:35,500
I know I should, dammit!

1287
00:56:35,583 --> 00:56:37,875
Do what you will, then.
Boil me. Roast me.

1288
00:56:37,958 --> 00:56:40,083
Do what you want, I don't care.

1289
00:56:40,166 --> 00:56:42,583
[BALLOON DOG] Aw, come on.
Don't let it get ya down.

1290
00:56:42,666 --> 00:56:44,625
It can talk!

1291
00:56:44,708 --> 00:56:47,125
[BALLOON DOG]
You can call me... Hm...

1292
00:56:47,208 --> 00:56:49,666
Oh! How about Mr. Kimidori?

1293
00:56:49,750 --> 00:56:51,875
It is the color of
my body, after all.

1294
00:56:51,958 --> 00:56:54,916
[ASAKURA] I have to address a
balloon dog as "mister," now?

1295
00:56:55,000 --> 00:56:56,375
Preparations complete.

1296
00:56:56,458 --> 00:56:57,791
Wait. Preparations?

1297
00:56:57,875 --> 00:56:58,916
There's so much happening,

1298
00:56:59,000 --> 00:57:00,666
I don't know what's
going on anymore!

1299
00:57:00,750 --> 00:57:03,625
Help! I'm floating!
Get me down from here!

1300
00:57:03,708 --> 00:57:06,458
By injecting a gas into it
which is lighter than air,

1301
00:57:06,541 --> 00:57:09,333
the balloon attains
the ability to float.

1302
00:57:09,416 --> 00:57:11,125
[MR. KIMIDORI]
Interesting phenomenon.

1303
00:57:11,208 --> 00:57:13,166
What kind of gas
did you put in it?

1304
00:57:13,250 --> 00:57:15,125
[NAGATO]
I extracted hydrogen from water,

1305
00:57:15,208 --> 00:57:16,458
and then I injec--

1306
00:57:40,000 --> 00:57:41,666
[HARUHI]
Here we g--!

1307
00:57:41,750 --> 00:57:42,833
[HARUHI groaning]

1308
00:57:51,375 --> 00:57:52,708
Hi everyone!

1309
00:57:52,791 --> 00:57:54,375
Drop what you're doin' and
grab those pots and pans,

1310
00:57:54,458 --> 00:57:57,375
'cause it's time for "Haruhi
Suzumiya's Simple Cooking Show"!

1311
00:57:57,458 --> 00:57:59,083
Yay!

1312
00:57:59,166 --> 00:58:01,083
The topic for today's
show is easy to make,

1313
00:58:01,166 --> 00:58:03,833
super nutritious, healthy,
fresh, rich, simple,

1314
00:58:03,916 --> 00:58:05,416
and inexpensive cooking!

1315
00:58:05,500 --> 00:58:08,750
Wow... That sounds
ambitious and nutritious.

1316
00:58:08,833 --> 00:58:12,000
For today's recipe, we're gonna
have to boil some instant ramen.

1317
00:58:12,083 --> 00:58:14,541
Hey! Isn't this supposed
to be a healthy recipe?!

1318
00:58:14,625 --> 00:58:17,000
But you'll have to
open the package first!

1319
00:58:17,083 --> 00:58:18,250
Yuki!

1320
00:58:18,333 --> 00:58:19,958
[KYON gasps]

1321
00:58:20,041 --> 00:58:21,583
[KYON]
That was unnecessary.

1322
00:58:21,666 --> 00:58:24,291
That was completely,
and totally, unnecessary.

1323
00:58:25,250 --> 00:58:27,125
[HARUHI]
That sucks. It's all broken.

1324
00:58:27,208 --> 00:58:28,958
Looks like damaged goods.

1325
00:58:29,041 --> 00:58:30,583
[KYON] You know...
the thing with the katana

1326
00:58:30,666 --> 00:58:31,916
could also be to blame.

1327
00:58:32,000 --> 00:58:33,250
Oh, well. Whatever.

1328
00:58:33,333 --> 00:58:34,458
We can just skip the step

1329
00:58:34,541 --> 00:58:36,708
where Yuki chops it
all up into quarters.

1330
00:58:36,791 --> 00:58:38,291
[KYON]
You were gonna throw it again?!

1331
00:58:38,375 --> 00:58:40,583
Next, we place all
the pieces of ramen

1332
00:58:40,666 --> 00:58:42,375
into a pot of boiling water.

1333
00:58:42,458 --> 00:58:44,333
Then we're gonna let
it cook for 50 hours.

1334
00:58:44,416 --> 00:58:47,333
What?! Cooking it for
50 hours isn't simple!

1335
00:58:47,416 --> 00:58:48,458
Don't worry about it.

1336
00:58:48,541 --> 00:58:50,375
I've got a batch of
it already cooked.

1337
00:58:50,458 --> 00:58:51,875
It'll look simple
to the audience,

1338
00:58:51,958 --> 00:58:53,375
but they'll never
know the truth.

1339
00:58:53,458 --> 00:58:54,833
That's not the problem!

1340
00:58:54,916 --> 00:58:57,625
[HARUHI] Mikuru! Bring the
you-know-what over here!

1341
00:58:57,708 --> 00:58:59,833
Oh! Okay!

1342
00:58:59,916 --> 00:59:02,041
[grunts]

1343
00:59:02,125 --> 00:59:04,125
[screams]

1344
00:59:06,583 --> 00:59:08,375
[HARUHI] Okay. We're
just gonna move on...

1345
00:59:08,458 --> 00:59:11,958
Miss Asahina. Duck down,
you're in the shot.

1346
00:59:12,041 --> 00:59:13,666
[HARUHI]
We put the noodles in a bowl.

1347
00:59:13,750 --> 00:59:16,083
Boiling them for 50 hours
has turned them all mushy,

1348
00:59:16,166 --> 00:59:18,750
but here's the good thing!
Now they're easier to digest,

1349
00:59:18,833 --> 00:59:20,541
so they're even better for you!

1350
00:59:20,625 --> 00:59:22,250
So, hang on a sec...

1351
00:59:22,333 --> 00:59:23,583
The noodles in that bowl were

1352
00:59:23,666 --> 00:59:25,125
cooked the right
amount of time, but...

1353
00:59:25,208 --> 00:59:27,375
Oh, never mind.
I get where this is going.

1354
00:59:27,458 --> 00:59:28,625
[HARUHI]
Let's set this aside for now,

1355
00:59:28,708 --> 00:59:30,625
and get ready to put on
the finishing touches!

1356
00:59:30,708 --> 00:59:32,500
I don't know 'bout you,
but I'm tired.

1357
00:59:32,583 --> 00:59:34,750
I'll be right back
after these commercials.

1358
00:59:34,833 --> 00:59:36,583
Wait! We've got commercials?!

1359
00:59:36,958 --> 00:59:38,166
[HARUHI]
You can do it!

1360
00:59:39,458 --> 00:59:40,625
[KYON]
Hm?

1361
00:59:40,708 --> 00:59:43,708
Hey, Nagato. What's up
with the katana anyway?

1362
00:59:43,791 --> 00:59:45,166
I can explain that!

1363
00:59:45,250 --> 00:59:47,291
Miss Suzumiya wanted a
really sharp kitchen knife

1364
00:59:47,375 --> 00:59:48,500
to have on set today.

1365
00:59:48,583 --> 00:59:50,291
So I got in touch
with my organization,

1366
00:59:50,375 --> 00:59:51,541
and they gave me that.

1367
00:59:51,625 --> 00:59:53,708
Uh! Are you trying to
get someone killed?!

1368
00:59:53,791 --> 00:59:55,583
[chuckles]

1369
00:59:55,666 --> 00:59:58,125
I've never handled a
real-life katana before.

1370
00:59:58,208 --> 01:00:00,958
Now that I'm holding one, I sort
of feel like cutting something.

1371
01:00:01,041 --> 01:00:02,458
If you don't mind,

1372
01:00:02,541 --> 01:00:04,500
would you please point that
at someone else for a while?

1373
01:00:04,583 --> 01:00:06,208
Homing mode has been activated.

1374
01:00:06,291 --> 01:00:09,000
You are now able to cut
a target any way you wish.

1375
01:00:09,083 --> 01:00:10,375
[KYON]
Yeah?

1376
01:00:10,458 --> 01:00:11,791
[KOIZUMI] Why don't you try
carving a human figure

1377
01:00:11,875 --> 01:00:13,291
out of this daikon?

1378
01:00:13,791 --> 01:00:15,166
Okay. Here goes no--

1379
01:00:15,250 --> 01:00:16,666
[KYON yelps]

1380
01:00:16,750 --> 01:00:18,666
Carving a detailed form will
cause a great deal of stress

1381
01:00:18,750 --> 01:00:20,083
on the wrists.

1382
01:00:20,166 --> 01:00:23,166
It is very dangerous for
humans to use cutlery.

1383
01:00:23,250 --> 01:00:24,916
[KOIZUMI]
Yes... Cutlery...

1384
01:00:25,000 --> 01:00:27,416
His wrists were bending in
all sorts of interesting ways,

1385
01:00:27,500 --> 01:00:28,750
weren't they?

1386
01:00:28,833 --> 01:00:31,041
Can you handle it without
incident, Miss Nagato?

1387
01:00:31,125 --> 01:00:32,083
[NAGATO]
Of course.

1388
01:00:34,500 --> 01:00:37,166
I can carve miniture
figures out of anything.

1389
01:00:37,250 --> 01:00:38,583
[KOIZUMI]
That's amazing.

1390
01:00:38,666 --> 01:00:40,208
Okay! Here I go again.

1391
01:00:40,291 --> 01:00:42,250
You don't know when
to give up, do you?

1392
01:00:42,333 --> 01:00:44,416
Heh. After watching
Nagato do it,

1393
01:00:44,500 --> 01:00:47,208
I figured out exactly where
I went wrong the last time.

1394
01:00:47,291 --> 01:00:49,416
Okay, then.
If you really want to.

1395
01:00:49,500 --> 01:00:51,000
[KYON]
You have to do the cutting

1396
01:00:51,083 --> 01:00:53,083
while the target's
still in the--

1397
01:00:53,166 --> 01:00:54,833
[screams]

1398
01:00:54,916 --> 01:00:56,625
--[screaming continues]
--[KOIZUMI] And he's spinning...

1399
01:00:56,708 --> 01:00:58,208
[sighs]

1400
01:00:58,291 --> 01:01:01,083
Okay, we're back. So let's hurry
up and finish the soup already.

1401
01:01:01,166 --> 01:01:02,291
[KYON]
She's bored...

1402
01:01:02,375 --> 01:01:03,541
I got a bunch of healthy
lookin' things here,

1403
01:01:03,625 --> 01:01:05,000
so I'm just gonna throw 'em in.

1404
01:01:05,083 --> 01:01:06,500
That's too vague!

1405
01:01:06,583 --> 01:01:08,666
Cover it up, and let the whole
thing cook for five days!

1406
01:01:08,750 --> 01:01:10,041
Five days?!

1407
01:01:10,125 --> 01:01:12,875
Okay, Mikuru. Try it again,
but without spilling!

1408
01:01:14,208 --> 01:01:16,333
[MIKURU grunting]

1409
01:01:16,416 --> 01:01:18,666
[MIKURU] The last time
I did this, I messed up.

1410
01:01:18,750 --> 01:01:21,916
But this time, I'm going
to do my job properly!

1411
01:01:22,000 --> 01:01:23,458
[KYON, HARUHI]
Uh?!

1412
01:01:23,541 --> 01:01:25,500
[KYON, HARUHI sigh]

1413
01:01:48,291 --> 01:01:49,916
[HARUHI]
Here we g--!

1414
01:01:50,000 --> 01:01:51,208
[HARUHI groaning]

1415
01:01:59,333 --> 01:02:01,500
[MIKURU]
Oh...

1416
01:02:05,458 --> 01:02:13,333
--[TSURUYA yells]
--[MIKURU screams]

1417
01:02:18,541 --> 01:02:21,083
[HARUHI]
Hm... Cherry blossoms.

1418
01:02:21,166 --> 01:02:24,375
Cherry blossom petals,
fluttering to the ground.

1419
01:02:24,458 --> 01:02:25,083
Blood spraying.

1420
01:02:25,166 --> 01:02:26,583
Uh?!

1421
01:02:26,666 --> 01:02:30,458
[HARUHI] Digging a hole...
Burying. Under a cherry tree.

1422
01:02:30,541 --> 01:02:32,791
I've got it!
A cherry blossom party!

1423
01:02:32,875 --> 01:02:34,541
Okay. Let's talk
about how you went from

1424
01:02:34,625 --> 01:02:35,625
what you were thinking just now

1425
01:02:35,708 --> 01:02:37,708
to having a cherry
blossom party.

1426
01:02:37,791 --> 01:02:38,875
[HARUHI sighs]

1427
01:02:38,958 --> 01:02:41,000
You'll never go far
with that attitude.

1428
01:02:41,083 --> 01:02:42,833
[KYON] Please don't
lecture me like that.

1429
01:02:42,916 --> 01:02:44,500
I'm not your son.

1430
01:02:44,583 --> 01:02:46,750
You'll always be a
subordinate Brigade member

1431
01:02:46,833 --> 01:02:48,250
if you don't change your ways.

1432
01:02:48,333 --> 01:02:50,500
Gotcha. I'm okay
with that though.

1433
01:02:50,583 --> 01:02:52,500
Really, I am, Mother.

1434
01:02:52,583 --> 01:02:54,791
I'm not your mother!
You wanna get smacked?!

1435
01:02:54,875 --> 01:02:55,958
[KYON]
You already smacked me!

1436
01:02:56,041 --> 01:02:57,708
Then I'm gonna call you father!

1437
01:02:57,791 --> 01:03:00,166
What are you talking about?!
Calm down!

1438
01:03:00,250 --> 01:03:01,708
[HARUHI]
You asked for it, Kyon!

1439
01:03:01,791 --> 01:03:05,125
Now I'm gonna show you just
how incompetent you really are!

1440
01:03:05,208 --> 01:03:06,708
Hey, Koizumi!

1441
01:03:06,791 --> 01:03:07,958
Did you call me?

1442
01:03:08,041 --> 01:03:09,625
[HARUHI] Mm-hm. Could
you come here for a sec?

1443
01:03:09,708 --> 01:03:11,333
This and that, and
that and this.

1444
01:03:11,416 --> 01:03:14,166
And then, after all that, what
would your conclusion be?

1445
01:03:14,250 --> 01:03:15,208
Cherry blossom party.

1446
01:03:15,291 --> 01:03:16,375
That was fast!

1447
01:03:16,458 --> 01:03:18,666
It wasn't terribly
hard to decipher it.

1448
01:03:18,750 --> 01:03:20,000
[KYON]
Oh. Yeah?

1449
01:03:30,333 --> 01:03:31,458
Well. How did I do?

1450
01:03:31,541 --> 01:03:32,916
Awesome job, Number 2!

1451
01:03:33,000 --> 01:03:35,041
I get it. You guys
are my enemies.

1452
01:03:35,125 --> 01:03:37,625
Okay! Let's go have a
cherry blossom party!

1453
01:03:37,708 --> 01:03:39,166
I refuse to go!

1454
01:03:39,250 --> 01:03:41,208
Koizumi, do you know of any
good places where we could go

1455
01:03:41,291 --> 01:03:42,541
for somethin' like this?

1456
01:03:42,625 --> 01:03:44,708
[KYON] Aren't you even
gonna try to convince me?

1457
01:03:44,791 --> 01:03:48,041
The thing is, anywhere we go
is probably gonna be crowded.

1458
01:03:48,125 --> 01:03:49,791
It's unfortunate, but true.

1459
01:03:49,875 --> 01:03:52,041
The best thing for us would
be if we could find a place

1460
01:03:52,125 --> 01:03:53,250
that's privately owned.

1461
01:03:53,333 --> 01:03:55,250
You can't dig holes
on private property.

1462
01:03:55,333 --> 01:03:56,791
Wherever we go,

1463
01:03:56,875 --> 01:03:59,333
we have to make sure digging
holes is okay with the owners.

1464
01:03:59,416 --> 01:04:00,875
That's true.

1465
01:04:00,958 --> 01:04:02,458
[KYON]
Just throwing this out there,

1466
01:04:02,541 --> 01:04:05,958
but maybe the hole digging thing
isn't really all that important?

1467
01:04:06,041 --> 01:04:08,541
[TSURUYA] Ha, ha. I heard what
you guys were talking about.

1468
01:04:08,625 --> 01:04:10,791
[gasps] Hey, I know that voice.

1469
01:04:10,875 --> 01:04:12,375
[KYON]
Tsuru-- Huh?

1470
01:04:12,458 --> 01:04:13,250
[HARUHI]
Mikuru?

1471
01:04:13,333 --> 01:04:14,250
[MIKURU]
Hm?

1472
01:04:14,333 --> 01:04:16,291
Miss Tsuruya?!
Where did you go?!

1473
01:04:16,375 --> 01:04:17,625
Don't disappear like that!

1474
01:04:17,708 --> 01:04:20,125
She just was just here, I swear.

1475
01:04:20,500 --> 01:04:22,625
[TSURUYA]
Ha, ha. Sorry about that.

1476
01:04:22,708 --> 01:04:23,791
[KYON]
Uh?! Sneaky!

1477
01:04:23,875 --> 01:04:25,583
I didn't mean to scare you.

1478
01:04:25,666 --> 01:04:27,500
I'm training for an
upcoming battle, though,

1479
01:04:27,583 --> 01:04:29,166
so I gotta stay sharp.

1480
01:04:29,250 --> 01:04:32,000
Anyway, it sounds like you guys
are trying to find a good place

1481
01:04:32,083 --> 01:04:34,166
to go look at cherry
blossoms, right?

1482
01:04:34,250 --> 01:04:36,000
[HARUHI] And a place
where we can dig a hole.

1483
01:04:36,083 --> 01:04:38,166
Then I've got the
perfect spot for you!

1484
01:04:38,250 --> 01:04:39,541
It's in the cherry
blossom section of

1485
01:04:39,625 --> 01:04:42,125
my private Tsuryua
Park Number 32.

1486
01:04:42,208 --> 01:04:44,541
[KYON] Whoa! What
doesn't this girl have?!

1487
01:04:44,625 --> 01:04:46,125
I like to keep it
on the down-low,

1488
01:04:46,208 --> 01:04:48,708
'cause the place has sort
of a sinister past to it.

1489
01:04:48,791 --> 01:04:50,833
You'll find something
if you dig deep enough.

1490
01:04:50,916 --> 01:04:52,208
[KYON]
A sinister what?!

1491
01:04:52,291 --> 01:04:55,083
[HARUHI] Right on! We're
gonna go there this weekend!

1492
01:04:55,166 --> 01:04:58,708
[ALL cheering]

1493
01:05:19,375 --> 01:05:21,000
[HARUHI]
Here we g--!

1494
01:05:21,083 --> 01:05:22,291
[HARUHI groaning]

1495
01:05:25,916 --> 01:05:27,166
[KYON grunts]

1496
01:05:27,250 --> 01:05:29,125
[KYON sighs]

1497
01:05:29,208 --> 01:05:30,166
Huh?

1498
01:05:31,541 --> 01:05:33,416
[HARUHI] Okay, Kyon. This
spot feels weird enough.

1499
01:05:33,500 --> 01:05:34,541
Start diggin'!

1500
01:05:34,625 --> 01:05:35,916
[KYON]
It's gonna take forever.

1501
01:05:36,000 --> 01:05:38,250
Would you relax? I can get
the others to come over

1502
01:05:38,333 --> 01:05:40,708
and help you out, so you'll
be done before you know it.

1503
01:05:40,791 --> 01:05:42,083
I think I get it.

1504
01:05:42,166 --> 01:05:44,083
Basically, everyone
else digs and you don't.

1505
01:05:44,166 --> 01:05:45,500
Yep! You know it.

1506
01:05:47,125 --> 01:05:50,166
Well, she did get the others to
come over here, that's for sure.

1507
01:05:50,250 --> 01:05:52,291
--But they're not much help.
--[GIRLS laughing]

1508
01:05:53,583 --> 01:05:55,833
Haruhi's playing
mahjong with the guys.

1509
01:05:55,916 --> 01:05:58,291
The girls go bored
and they came over.

1510
01:05:58,375 --> 01:06:00,375
Geez. They're acting
like little kids!

1511
01:06:00,458 --> 01:06:02,166
[MIKURU]
Hey, Kyon, look!

1512
01:06:02,250 --> 01:06:04,041
We found something strange.

1513
01:06:04,125 --> 01:06:06,083
[KYON]
Hm? Let's see.

1514
01:06:06,166 --> 01:06:09,416
Wow. It's awfully pretty. I've
never seen anything like it.

1515
01:06:09,500 --> 01:06:10,875
Maybe it's a jewel.

1516
01:06:10,958 --> 01:06:12,791
[NAGATO]
It is not.

1517
01:06:12,875 --> 01:06:14,208
That is no jewel.

1518
01:06:14,291 --> 01:06:17,125
A subspecies of the Data
Integration Thought Entity

1519
01:06:17,208 --> 01:06:18,416
lives within it.

1520
01:06:18,500 --> 01:06:21,375
It coexists with the
cherry trees in this area.

1521
01:06:21,458 --> 01:06:23,250
It clouds the mind of its prey,

1522
01:06:23,333 --> 01:06:25,541
taking away its
ability to reason.

1523
01:06:25,625 --> 01:06:27,916
It forces its prey
to stay in the area,

1524
01:06:28,000 --> 01:06:30,041
taking care of the cherry trees.

1525
01:06:30,125 --> 01:06:31,291
When the prey dies,

1526
01:06:31,375 --> 01:06:34,166
it decays and becomes
nutrients for the tree.

1527
01:06:34,250 --> 01:06:37,916
That is the reason why
this area has a sinister past.

1528
01:06:38,000 --> 01:06:39,750
Heh! You must be kidding!

1529
01:06:39,833 --> 01:06:41,958
Your story was so
long, I got lost!

1530
01:06:42,041 --> 01:06:43,750
Me, too!

1531
01:06:43,833 --> 01:06:45,000
Uh!

1532
01:06:49,333 --> 01:06:51,833
Does anyone know what we
were just talking about?

1533
01:06:51,916 --> 01:06:52,833
[NAGATO]
I do not.

1534
01:06:52,916 --> 01:06:53,791
[HARUHI]
Mikuru!

1535
01:06:53,875 --> 01:06:55,333
--[MIKURU] Huh?
--[KYON] Hm?

1536
01:06:55,416 --> 01:06:58,250
I'm sorry, but Miss Suzumiya's
calling for us to come back.

1537
01:06:58,333 --> 01:07:00,208
Are you going to
be okay if we go?

1538
01:07:00,291 --> 01:07:03,041
Yeah, sure. If you guys get
bored hanging out with her,

1539
01:07:03,125 --> 01:07:04,291
come on back.

1540
01:07:07,833 --> 01:07:09,541
Well, here I am.

1541
01:07:09,625 --> 01:07:11,041
Please tell me
you've got some idea

1542
01:07:11,125 --> 01:07:12,833
about how to get
this digging done?

1543
01:07:12,916 --> 01:07:15,833
Yes. As a matter of fact,
I've called in for some backup.

1544
01:07:17,791 --> 01:07:19,208
Uh!

1545
01:07:19,291 --> 01:07:21,541
I'm a taxi driver, just
passing through.

1546
01:07:21,625 --> 01:07:22,833
Arakawa?!

1547
01:07:22,916 --> 01:07:25,250
You were driving rather
frantically there.

1548
01:07:25,333 --> 01:07:26,875
I hope that
everything's all right.

1549
01:07:26,958 --> 01:07:29,750
Well, this is the
Tsuruya family's property.

1550
01:07:29,833 --> 01:07:32,375
The security was
tighter than I expected.

1551
01:07:32,458 --> 01:07:34,333
And, if my calculations
are correct,

1552
01:07:34,416 --> 01:07:36,750
I can only stay about
three minutes or so.

1553
01:07:36,833 --> 01:07:37,875
[KOIZUMI]
Hm.

1554
01:07:37,958 --> 01:07:39,666
[KYON]
I'm totally lost.

1555
01:07:39,750 --> 01:07:42,000
Three minutes should be
plenty of time for this!

1556
01:07:42,083 --> 01:07:45,041
You're gonna make Mr. Arakawa
dig a hole in three minutes?!

1557
01:07:45,125 --> 01:07:47,916
Not at all. In fact, I have
something else in mind.

1558
01:07:48,000 --> 01:07:50,125
Look. See for yourself.

1559
01:07:54,541 --> 01:07:55,791
[KYON]
A bomb?!

1560
01:08:01,833 --> 01:08:04,291
Hello. I'm just a skydiver
who's passing through.

1561
01:08:04,375 --> 01:08:05,458
Miss Mori?!

1562
01:08:05,541 --> 01:08:08,041
I had no choice but
to crash-land here.

1563
01:08:08,125 --> 01:08:10,666
And, silly me, I forgot
my parachute.

1564
01:08:10,750 --> 01:08:13,750
You don't say? That's rather
clumsy of you, isn't it?

1565
01:08:13,833 --> 01:08:15,250
[KYON]
Clumsy?!

1566
01:08:15,333 --> 01:08:18,000
I wouldn't call skydiving
without a parachute "clumsy"!

1567
01:08:18,083 --> 01:08:20,958
I happen to be a taxi driver.
I could give you give you a ride

1568
01:08:21,041 --> 01:08:22,958
back to town in my
cab if you like.

1569
01:08:23,041 --> 01:08:25,250
Actually, we're out
of time, so I insist.

1570
01:08:25,333 --> 01:08:28,541
Why thank you. I can't
refuse an offer like that.

1571
01:08:28,625 --> 01:08:30,291
It was nice meeting
you, gentlemen.

1572
01:08:30,375 --> 01:08:31,750
I hate to crash
and run like this,

1573
01:08:31,833 --> 01:08:33,916
but we really must be going.

1574
01:08:38,083 --> 01:08:40,333
They leave a path of
destruction wherever they go.

1575
01:08:40,416 --> 01:08:43,125
[KYON] What's up with you and
the corny action movie dialogue?

1576
01:08:43,208 --> 01:08:44,500
And button your shirt!

1577
01:08:44,583 --> 01:08:46,833
[HARUHI]
Kyon! We heard a big explosion!

1578
01:08:46,916 --> 01:08:48,333
Did something happen?

1579
01:08:48,416 --> 01:08:51,208
Whoa! Did you dig
this by yourself?

1580
01:08:51,291 --> 01:08:53,041
Amazing job, Kyon!

1581
01:08:53,125 --> 01:08:54,750
It's really amazing!

1582
01:08:54,833 --> 01:08:56,875
Super amazing, Kyon!

1583
01:08:58,666 --> 01:09:01,791
[KYON]
Yeah... Well...

1584
01:09:01,875 --> 01:09:04,375
Let's just say I
did it on my own.

1585
01:09:09,958 --> 01:09:12,333
[TSURUYA]
Right. Sure.

1586
01:09:12,416 --> 01:09:13,541
But that doesn't explain how

1587
01:09:13,625 --> 01:09:15,791
they breached our
security so easily.

1588
01:09:15,875 --> 01:09:17,125
[KYON]
Later, I heard Miss Tsuruya

1589
01:09:17,208 --> 01:09:18,833
make an unsettling phone call.

1590
01:09:18,916 --> 01:09:20,000
To be continued...

1591
01:09:20,083 --> 01:09:21,041
Wait! What?!

1592
01:09:40,750 --> 01:09:42,291
[HARUHI]
Here we g--!

1593
01:09:42,375 --> 01:09:43,625
[HARUHI groaning]

1594
01:09:48,375 --> 01:09:50,125
Listen up!
We're gonna have ourselves

1595
01:09:50,208 --> 01:09:51,541
a Christmas party today!

1596
01:09:51,625 --> 01:09:53,916
Yay! Yay! Ha, ha, ha, ha!

1597
01:09:54,000 --> 01:09:56,041
[HARUHI]
Dumbass!

1598
01:09:56,125 --> 01:09:58,000
You better take
this party seriously,

1599
01:09:58,083 --> 01:10:00,166
'cause if you don't, they're
gonna come and kill us all!

1600
01:10:00,250 --> 01:10:02,500
Who are you talking about?!

1601
01:10:02,583 --> 01:10:03,708
[HARUHI]
I'm talking about people

1602
01:10:03,791 --> 01:10:05,375
who stalk rooftops at night.

1603
01:10:05,458 --> 01:10:07,458
They carry sack full of
presents on their backs,

1604
01:10:07,541 --> 01:10:10,083
and sneak in and out of houses
without anyone noticing

1605
01:10:10,166 --> 01:10:11,541
they've been there.

1606
01:10:11,625 --> 01:10:14,083
They're the elite members
of a mysterious organization

1607
01:10:14,166 --> 01:10:16,791
who carry out their secret
mission once a year.

1608
01:10:16,875 --> 01:10:18,000
Known as...

1609
01:10:18,083 --> 01:10:19,458
...Santa Claus!

1610
01:10:19,541 --> 01:10:21,375
--[MIKURU screams]
--The SOS Brigade is the only

1611
01:10:21,458 --> 01:10:24,208
thing standing between them
and the unsuspecting public.

1612
01:10:24,291 --> 01:10:26,416
Get ready, 'cause they're
coming for us tonight!

1613
01:10:26,500 --> 01:10:28,000
You're kidding!

1614
01:10:28,083 --> 01:10:30,833
The only chance we have beating
the threat know as Santa Claus

1615
01:10:30,916 --> 01:10:33,125
is to have a full-proof
battle plan.

1616
01:10:33,208 --> 01:10:34,791
So here it is, everyone!

1617
01:10:34,875 --> 01:10:36,583
The Plan!

1618
01:10:36,666 --> 01:10:38,500
First, we're gonna
throw him off our trail.

1619
01:10:38,583 --> 01:10:41,000
We put up a sign in the window
of the Computer Club's room

1620
01:10:41,083 --> 01:10:42,541
to make 'em think it's ours.

1621
01:10:42,625 --> 01:10:45,333
Next, Kyon's gonna hide in
the room and wait by himself

1622
01:10:45,416 --> 01:10:47,416
until the target shows up.

1623
01:10:47,500 --> 01:10:50,041
The rest of us are gonna be
here in the SOS Brigade's room

1624
01:10:50,125 --> 01:10:52,083
partying until we
run out of cake.

1625
01:10:52,166 --> 01:10:53,666
We have to be careful though.

1626
01:10:53,750 --> 01:10:57,666
If we get too loud, Santa might
here us and abort the mission.

1627
01:10:57,750 --> 01:10:58,708
That is all.

1628
01:10:58,791 --> 01:11:00,916
Any objections? Besides Kyon.

1629
01:11:01,000 --> 01:11:02,500
[KYON]
I can't even object now?!

1630
01:11:02,583 --> 01:11:04,166
We're gonna need all
the help we can get,

1631
01:11:04,250 --> 01:11:06,708
so I got Miss Tsuruya
to give us a hand.

1632
01:11:06,791 --> 01:11:09,000
Hi guys! Ready to party?!

1633
01:11:09,083 --> 01:11:11,083
If we end up having a
show down with Santa,

1634
01:11:11,166 --> 01:11:13,375
she's gonna step up and
turn the tables on him.

1635
01:11:13,458 --> 01:11:15,375
[laughs] I can handle him!

1636
01:11:15,458 --> 01:11:18,750
I can't wait to practice my
fighting technique on that guy!

1637
01:11:18,833 --> 01:11:21,791
I'm gonna become a master of the
Tsuruya-family Fighting Style

1638
01:11:21,875 --> 01:11:23,041
when I turn 19!

1639
01:11:23,125 --> 01:11:24,375
[KYON]
No way!

1640
01:11:24,458 --> 01:11:26,541
[TSURUYA] What's up, Kyon?
Don't you believe me?

1641
01:11:26,625 --> 01:11:29,833
I don't. It's pretty obvious
you made that last part up.

1642
01:11:29,916 --> 01:11:32,041
[TSURUYA]
Okay then, take a look at this.

1643
01:11:32,125 --> 01:11:33,375
[KYON]
What am I looking at?

1644
01:11:33,458 --> 01:11:35,166
[TSURUYA] It's a picture
of when I fought a bear

1645
01:11:35,250 --> 01:11:36,166
in the mountains.

1646
01:11:36,250 --> 01:11:38,208
Wow! Cool!

1647
01:11:38,291 --> 01:11:39,666
That's so fake!

1648
01:11:40,958 --> 01:11:43,333
Perfect. Santa Claus
is gonna see this sign,

1649
01:11:43,416 --> 01:11:45,625
think we're here, and come
right through this window.

1650
01:11:45,708 --> 01:11:47,041
You sure that'll work?

1651
01:11:47,125 --> 01:11:49,791
Now we just need to find a
good hiding place for you.

1652
01:11:49,875 --> 01:11:50,833
A-ha!

1653
01:11:51,958 --> 01:11:53,083
Here, put this on.

1654
01:11:53,166 --> 01:11:54,958
I absolutely refuse!

1655
01:11:55,041 --> 01:11:57,375
Your refusal has been
refused! Put it on!

1656
01:11:57,458 --> 01:11:58,875
[KYON]
You're evil.

1657
01:11:58,958 --> 01:12:01,833
Come on. It's okay. Don't be
such a baby. Just put it on.

1658
01:12:01,916 --> 01:12:03,333
You're gonna look great!

1659
01:12:03,416 --> 01:12:05,041
I don't think I'm gonna
care how I look

1660
01:12:05,125 --> 01:12:07,458
with that thing on my head.

1661
01:12:07,541 --> 01:12:09,000
[HARUHI laughing]

1662
01:12:09,083 --> 01:12:11,000
[KYON]
I wanna die now...

1663
01:12:16,875 --> 01:12:17,666
[TANIGUCHI sighs]

1664
01:12:17,750 --> 01:12:18,916
I can't believe I made it

1665
01:12:19,000 --> 01:12:21,666
all the way over here
without being spotted.

1666
01:12:21,750 --> 01:12:24,875
I'm finally gonna be able
to get rid of this kappa.

1667
01:12:24,958 --> 01:12:27,166
I picked the perfect
night to do this, too.

1668
01:12:27,250 --> 01:12:30,500
No one's gonna suspect
it's me in the get-up.

1669
01:12:30,583 --> 01:12:33,625
It's pretty risky with Suzumiya
and the others still here.

1670
01:12:33,708 --> 01:12:35,333
Whatever.
Tonight's the night

1671
01:12:35,416 --> 01:12:37,875
this freakin' kappa's
goin' home for good.

1672
01:12:37,958 --> 01:12:40,208
All right. Here I go.

1673
01:12:41,125 --> 01:12:42,375
[KYON sighs]

1674
01:12:42,458 --> 01:12:45,875
I wonder if Santa's really
gonna show up tonight.

1675
01:12:45,958 --> 01:12:49,458
I feel so stupid. Everyone's
next door having a good time.

1676
01:12:49,541 --> 01:12:50,833
What the hell.

1677
01:12:50,916 --> 01:12:53,333
But if I wasn't here, I'd be
home spending Christmas

1678
01:12:53,416 --> 01:12:54,750
with my little sister.

1679
01:12:54,833 --> 01:12:57,625
That wouldn't be
much fun, either.

1680
01:12:57,708 --> 01:12:58,583
Huh?!

1681
01:12:59,500 --> 01:13:01,375
Who... Wha... I...? Santa...?

1682
01:13:01,458 --> 01:13:04,333
[TANIGUCHI whimpers]

1683
01:13:04,416 --> 01:13:06,208
What is that?!

1684
01:13:06,291 --> 01:13:07,208
[ALL]
Huh?

1685
01:13:07,291 --> 01:13:08,666
What was that?!

1686
01:13:08,750 --> 01:13:10,125
[TANIGUCHI whimpers]

1687
01:13:10,208 --> 01:13:11,166
[HARUHI gasps]

1688
01:13:15,000 --> 01:13:24,041
[HARUHI]
It's Santa!

1689
01:13:25,375 --> 01:13:26,541
[TANIGUCHI]
Uh!

1690
01:13:28,291 --> 01:13:31,458
[TANIGUCHI grunting]

1691
01:13:35,125 --> 01:13:36,625
[KYON]
He's so big... and ran away.

1692
01:13:36,708 --> 01:13:39,541
I think he's trying to find
a hiding place on campus.

1693
01:13:39,625 --> 01:13:42,166
Come on, guys! Let's catch him!

1694
01:13:42,250 --> 01:13:45,625
[KOIZUMI] Interesting. Miss
Suzumiya was picturing Santa

1695
01:13:45,708 --> 01:13:49,541
to be this monstrous person,
so that's exactly what she got.

1696
01:13:49,625 --> 01:13:51,750
Her power took what
was in her imagination,

1697
01:13:51,833 --> 01:13:54,333
and transformed
Taniguchi's body.

1698
01:13:55,500 --> 01:13:57,458
It's no use. I can't catch him.

1699
01:13:57,541 --> 01:13:59,375
For a big guy,
he can really move.

1700
01:13:59,458 --> 01:14:01,541
Hm. I know. But we
can slow down now

1701
01:14:01,625 --> 01:14:03,125
'cause he's heading
right into my trap.

1702
01:14:03,208 --> 01:14:04,375
What trap?!

1703
01:14:04,458 --> 01:14:05,666
[KYON]
Miss Tsuruya!

1704
01:14:05,750 --> 01:14:07,250
Like I said.

1705
01:14:07,333 --> 01:14:09,708
Leave it to me.
I can handle this guy!

1706
01:14:09,791 --> 01:14:10,916
[TANIGUCHI groaning]

1707
01:14:11,000 --> 01:14:11,958
Now!

1708
01:14:13,125 --> 01:14:16,416
[TANIGUCHI groans]

1709
01:14:16,500 --> 01:14:18,291
Awesome job, Miss Tsuruya!

1710
01:14:18,375 --> 01:14:19,625
And you, too, Yuki!

1711
01:14:19,708 --> 01:14:22,291
[KYON] The Tsuruya-family
Fighting Style is real?

1712
01:14:22,375 --> 01:14:23,666
[TANIGUCHI grunting]

1713
01:14:23,750 --> 01:14:27,708
[HARUHI gasps] No... I can't
believe it. He's gone.

1714
01:14:27,791 --> 01:14:30,208
He just left his clothes
behind and ran away.

1715
01:14:30,291 --> 01:14:32,041
Was it safe to just let him go?

1716
01:14:32,125 --> 01:14:35,625
I neutralized the changes Miss
Suzamiya made to Santa's body.

1717
01:14:35,708 --> 01:14:38,208
[HARUHI whimpering]

1718
01:14:38,291 --> 01:14:43,500
Come back, Santa! Don't go!

1719
01:14:43,583 --> 01:14:49,208
[teeth chattering]

1720
01:14:49,291 --> 01:14:52,750
O-Okay. So... why am I naked?

1721
01:15:13,000 --> 01:15:14,750
[HARUHI]
Here we g--!

1722
01:15:14,833 --> 01:15:16,083
[HARUHI groaning]

1723
01:15:20,541 --> 01:15:23,250
[door opens]

1724
01:15:24,291 --> 01:15:25,666
I'm home.

1725
01:15:25,750 --> 01:15:29,500
Oh, no. This is terrible.
Mr. Kimidori has gone flat.

1726
01:15:29,583 --> 01:15:31,291
[MR. KIMIDORI]
It looks like the end for me.

1727
01:15:31,375 --> 01:15:33,875
I'd like to be bury at sea,
if you don't mind.

1728
01:15:33,958 --> 01:15:36,583
I cannot. If I threw a
balloon into the ocean,

1729
01:15:36,666 --> 01:15:38,833
it would destroy
the environment.

1730
01:15:40,500 --> 01:15:42,750
[ASAKURA] Miss Nagato didn't
believe any of it, did she?

1731
01:15:42,833 --> 01:15:45,541
[MR. KIMIDORI] Well, our
acting could've been better.

1732
01:15:45,625 --> 01:15:47,958
Anyway, would you please
blow me up again?

1733
01:15:48,041 --> 01:15:49,083
[ASAKURA]
Okay.

1734
01:15:53,291 --> 01:15:55,333
Mr. Kimidori pushed
me out of harm's way

1735
01:15:55,416 --> 01:15:57,958
and got stuck under
the refrigerator!

1736
01:15:58,041 --> 01:15:59,500
[MR. KIMIDORI]
The light's fading...

1737
01:15:59,583 --> 01:16:02,666
I want to be cremated and my
ashes scattered to the winds.

1738
01:16:02,750 --> 01:16:06,291
I can't burn a balloon because
of the toxins it would release!

1739
01:16:08,541 --> 01:16:11,333
[MR. KIMIDORI sighs]
We look pretty stupid right now.

1740
01:16:11,416 --> 01:16:13,375
[ASAKURA]
Might as well give up, then.

1741
01:16:13,458 --> 01:16:15,666
[MR. KIMIDORI] Would you please
pull out from under this thing?

1742
01:16:15,750 --> 01:16:17,750
Oh, I'm sorry. Of course.

1743
01:16:17,833 --> 01:16:19,833
[MR. KIMIDORI grunting]

1744
01:16:19,916 --> 01:16:21,958
Uh-oh. I think you're
caught on something.

1745
01:16:22,041 --> 01:16:24,041
I'm having a hard time
pulling you out.

1746
01:16:24,125 --> 01:16:25,208
Is something wrong?

1747
01:16:25,291 --> 01:16:26,458
Yes, Miss Nagato.

1748
01:16:26,541 --> 01:16:30,083
Mr. Kimidori is stuck
under the refrigerator.

1749
01:16:30,166 --> 01:16:31,458
[ASAKURA]
Careful!

1750
01:16:31,541 --> 01:16:33,833
If you pull too hard,
Mr. Kimidori is going to--

1751
01:16:33,916 --> 01:16:36,666
[screams]

1752
01:16:36,750 --> 01:16:38,000
[NAGATO]
Your dog is dead.

1753
01:16:38,083 --> 01:16:40,166
Mr. Kimidori!

1754
01:16:40,250 --> 01:16:41,375
It's all my fault!

1755
01:16:41,458 --> 01:16:43,208
If it wasn't for this
April Fool's prank,

1756
01:16:43,291 --> 01:16:46,791
he'd still be alive!
It's all my fault!

1757
01:16:46,875 --> 01:16:49,416
[NAGATO] You shouldn't
blame yourself, little one.

1758
01:16:52,500 --> 01:16:55,291
How dare you trick me?!

1759
01:17:17,125 --> 01:17:18,833
[HARUHI]
Here we g--!

1760
01:17:18,916 --> 01:17:20,208
[HARUHI groaning]

1761
01:17:23,125 --> 01:17:25,708
[HARUHI]
A live-action ESPer sentai show?

1762
01:17:25,791 --> 01:17:28,125
Yeah! It's up on the
roof of Marutsuru,

1763
01:17:28,208 --> 01:17:29,833
the store my family owns.

1764
01:17:29,916 --> 01:17:31,208
I got a bunch of free tickets,

1765
01:17:31,291 --> 01:17:33,166
so I thought you and the
others might like to go.

1766
01:17:33,250 --> 01:17:35,000
Well, that's really nice of you.

1767
01:17:35,083 --> 01:17:37,500
But I don't think I want
to see fake super-heroes.

1768
01:17:37,583 --> 01:17:39,833
--But if they were real-- Ah!
--[NAGATO] We're going.

1769
01:17:39,916 --> 01:17:44,000
Oh. Okay. If Yuki wants
to go, then I'm in, too.

1770
01:17:44,083 --> 01:17:45,458
Let's all go together.

1771
01:17:45,541 --> 01:17:46,500
[NAGATO]
Mm.

1772
01:17:51,000 --> 01:17:54,333
[CROWD cheers]

1773
01:17:54,416 --> 01:17:56,125
What's the deal with
all these people?

1774
01:17:56,208 --> 01:17:58,791
Don't tell me you've
never heard about this.

1775
01:17:58,875 --> 01:18:00,208
Every year,

1776
01:18:00,291 --> 01:18:03,041
the folks at Marutsuru produce
an amazing sentai show.

1777
01:18:03,125 --> 01:18:04,708
The fight scenes
are so incredible,

1778
01:18:04,791 --> 01:18:06,625
everyone in Japan
knows about it.

1779
01:18:06,708 --> 01:18:08,625
Every person here is
a fan of the show.

1780
01:18:08,708 --> 01:18:10,583
Now I get it.

1781
01:18:10,666 --> 01:18:12,791
That explains why the girls
are all in the front row

1782
01:18:12,875 --> 01:18:14,541
being loud and annoying.

1783
01:18:14,625 --> 01:18:15,875
Listen everyone!

1784
01:18:15,958 --> 01:18:18,000
Our heroes can't defeat
the monster by themselves!

1785
01:18:18,083 --> 01:18:21,083
I need your help to call the
only person who can save them.

1786
01:18:21,166 --> 01:18:22,208
All together!

1787
01:18:22,291 --> 01:18:24,500
--Mustache Mask!
--[CROWD] Mustache Mask!

1788
01:18:24,583 --> 01:18:26,916
They're heroes and they need
to ask the audience for help?!

1789
01:18:27,000 --> 01:18:30,041
[HOST] I don't think
he heard you! Louder!

1790
01:18:30,125 --> 01:18:31,625
I was gonna ask you this before,

1791
01:18:31,708 --> 01:18:34,125
but why are you doing
a jigsaw puzzle here?

1792
01:18:34,208 --> 01:18:36,458
Well, I knew we'd
have time to kill,

1793
01:18:36,541 --> 01:18:39,208
so I brought it to
keep us occupied.

1794
01:18:39,291 --> 01:18:41,791
[KYON] Two guys doing a
jigsaw puzzle on a Sunday?

1795
01:18:41,875 --> 01:18:43,083
How depressing.

1796
01:18:43,166 --> 01:18:44,250
And it's got roses on it.

1797
01:18:44,333 --> 01:18:46,166
[KOIZUMI]
Hey. You're wokin' on it, too.

1798
01:18:46,250 --> 01:18:49,791
Okay, monster.
Meet your newest opponent.

1799
01:18:49,875 --> 01:18:52,333
Holy crap! That's Mr. Arakawa!

1800
01:18:52,416 --> 01:18:55,458
Oh, look at that.
It is Mr. Arakawa.

1801
01:18:55,541 --> 01:18:57,250
Oh, and the monster's Miss Mori.

1802
01:18:57,333 --> 01:18:58,500
[KYON]
You're kidding?!

1803
01:18:58,583 --> 01:19:00,666
Is this another one of
their secret missions?!

1804
01:19:00,750 --> 01:19:02,125
[MONSTER roars]

1805
01:19:02,208 --> 01:19:03,083
Come on!

1806
01:19:03,166 --> 01:19:03,958
[MONSTER roars]

1807
01:19:04,041 --> 01:19:05,083
[ARAWAKA yells]

1808
01:19:06,833 --> 01:19:09,625
[MIKURU] The other sentai
are just cheering him on.

1809
01:19:09,708 --> 01:19:12,000
I wonder why they
don't help him.

1810
01:19:12,083 --> 01:19:14,000
Miss Tsuruya, why
aren't the others...

1811
01:19:14,083 --> 01:19:15,458
There it is again.

1812
01:19:15,541 --> 01:19:16,708
That feeling...

1813
01:19:18,375 --> 01:19:20,166
Miss Suzumi, why don't the--

1814
01:19:20,250 --> 01:19:22,375
[HARUHI]
Yuki! Get down from there!

1815
01:19:22,458 --> 01:19:26,166
You can't go on stage!
No! Come on!

1816
01:19:26,250 --> 01:19:28,875
[MIKURU] I'll just stand
here and enjoy the show.

1817
01:19:31,083 --> 01:19:32,083
That's it?

1818
01:19:32,166 --> 01:19:33,333
Someone else does
all the fighting,

1819
01:19:33,416 --> 01:19:34,625
but they get to kill it?

1820
01:19:34,708 --> 01:19:36,333
They always seem
to get the good part.

1821
01:19:36,416 --> 01:19:38,041
[HARUHI]
We're back!

1822
01:19:38,125 --> 01:19:40,083
Man, that was so cool!
Wasn't it?

1823
01:19:40,166 --> 01:19:42,583
You look like you were
really getting into to.

1824
01:19:42,666 --> 01:19:43,625
[HARUHI]
No, not really.

1825
01:19:43,708 --> 01:19:45,875
I just came because
Yuki wanted to.

1826
01:19:45,958 --> 01:19:47,291
Hey, could you watch my bag?

1827
01:19:47,375 --> 01:19:48,625
I'm gonna go get an autograph.

1828
01:19:48,708 --> 01:19:50,125
[KYON] Yeah.
You were definitely into it.

1829
01:19:50,208 --> 01:19:52,625
[HARUHI] Wait here for us.
We'll be back in a bit.

1830
01:19:52,708 --> 01:19:54,166
[KYON]
Huh?!

1831
01:19:54,250 --> 01:19:55,541
[MR. ARAKAWA]
Here you go, kid.

1832
01:19:55,625 --> 01:19:57,291
I love you Mustache Mask!

1833
01:19:57,375 --> 01:19:59,291
[HARUHI]
Darn it. We're last in line.

1834
01:19:59,375 --> 01:20:02,375
Mustache Mask is
really popular, isn't he?

1835
01:20:02,458 --> 01:20:03,416
Hm?

1836
01:20:05,000 --> 01:20:08,125
Hey, I'll be back in just a sec.
I have to use the restroom.

1837
01:20:08,208 --> 01:20:11,625
Okay. I'll get an autograph
for you if you're not back.

1838
01:20:11,708 --> 01:20:14,875
[MIKURU] Aren't the restrooms
the other way though?

1839
01:20:21,541 --> 01:20:24,333
I knew there was
something shady about you.

1840
01:20:24,416 --> 01:20:28,208
Those weird vibes I felt
gave you away, nyoro.

1841
01:20:28,291 --> 01:20:30,500
Now that we're here, we might
as well make the most of it,

1842
01:20:30,583 --> 01:20:31,875
don't you think?

1843
01:20:33,208 --> 01:20:36,125
Okay, get ready!
'Cause here I come!

1844
01:20:36,208 --> 01:20:39,083
Don't hold back.
I need a good workout today.

1845
01:20:41,125 --> 01:20:41,833
[TSURUYA]
Huh?

1846
01:20:41,916 --> 01:20:42,875
Uh!

1847
01:20:44,208 --> 01:20:45,500
That didn't work...

1848
01:20:45,583 --> 01:20:48,291
She can move pretty
fast in that costume.

1849
01:20:50,416 --> 01:20:53,458
[TSURUYA] What's up? All
she does is dodge my attacks.

1850
01:20:53,541 --> 01:20:55,791
She hasn't even
tried to fight back!

1851
01:20:56,541 --> 01:20:57,666
I know.

1852
01:20:57,750 --> 01:20:59,416
I'll try getting her
right when she lands.

1853
01:20:59,500 --> 01:21:01,166
She won't even
know what hit her.

1854
01:21:03,083 --> 01:21:05,875
And I'll keep hitting
her till she goes down!

1855
01:21:05,958 --> 01:21:06,916
[grunts]

1856
01:21:11,250 --> 01:21:13,041
[KOIZUMI]
This is amazing.

1857
01:21:13,125 --> 01:21:15,083
I can't believe we're
almost finished with it.

1858
01:21:15,166 --> 01:21:17,833
A hundred thousand
pieces is no joke.

1859
01:21:17,916 --> 01:21:20,000
Okay. Are you ready to do this?

1860
01:21:20,083 --> 01:21:23,833
Oh, yeah. We've come a long way,
and there's no turning back now.

1861
01:21:23,916 --> 01:21:27,541
One more piece and this
puzzle is officially finished.

1862
01:21:27,625 --> 01:21:29,208
Here goes.

1863
01:21:31,250 --> 01:21:34,500
[BOTH laughing]

1864
01:21:39,625 --> 01:21:41,083
Did I get her?

1865
01:21:41,166 --> 01:21:42,375
Huh?

1866
01:21:42,458 --> 01:21:43,750
Where'd she go?

1867
01:21:43,833 --> 01:21:45,708
[MORI] That was a wonderful
attack. I'm impressed.

1868
01:21:45,791 --> 01:21:46,916
[gasps]

1869
01:21:47,000 --> 01:21:48,375
[MORI] I thought I could
take you on wearing

1870
01:21:48,458 --> 01:21:49,791
that cumbersom outfit.

1871
01:21:49,875 --> 01:21:52,583
But now that it's off,
I'm feeling much better.

1872
01:21:52,666 --> 01:21:54,541
And since I'm in such
a good mood now,

1873
01:21:54,625 --> 01:21:57,666
I'd like to give you
a piece of advice.

1874
01:21:57,750 --> 01:21:58,916
Hey, little girl...

1875
01:21:59,000 --> 01:22:00,333
Watch your back!

1876
01:22:05,875 --> 01:22:09,416
Hey, we're back! Sorry
you had to wait so long.

1877
01:22:09,500 --> 01:22:10,458
Uh?

1878
01:22:14,750 --> 01:22:17,750
Hey, uh, Kyon... What's wrong?

1879
01:22:17,833 --> 01:22:19,416
Koizumi?

1880
01:22:22,666 --> 01:22:23,875
[MORI]
Hello, it's me.

1881
01:22:23,958 --> 01:22:25,916
I'm on my way back now.

1882
01:22:26,000 --> 01:22:27,916
I hope you set my
lunch aside for me.

1883
01:22:28,000 --> 01:22:30,208
I've worked up
quite an appetite.

1884
01:22:51,458 --> 01:22:53,000
[HARUHI]
Here we g--!

1885
01:22:53,083 --> 01:22:54,541
[HARUHI groaning]

1886
01:23:00,125 --> 01:23:01,083
Huh?

1887
01:23:06,000 --> 01:23:07,500
[ASAKURA]
Ah!

1888
01:23:07,583 --> 01:23:08,500
[MR. KIMIDORI chuckles]

1889
01:23:08,583 --> 01:23:09,833
Guess who?

1890
01:23:09,916 --> 01:23:11,541
I bet you're surprised to
see me floating around.

1891
01:23:11,625 --> 01:23:13,541
[ASAKURA] Haven't you got
anything better to do?

1892
01:23:13,625 --> 01:23:16,166
Why don't you help me
clean up around here?

1893
01:23:29,541 --> 01:23:30,541
Huh?

1894
01:23:31,458 --> 01:23:33,083
Uh...

1895
01:23:33,166 --> 01:23:35,000
Oh, seriously Miss Nagato.

1896
01:23:35,083 --> 01:23:37,458
Pick up your stuff after you've
finished playing with it.

1897
01:23:37,541 --> 01:23:38,916
[MR. KIMIDORI sighs]

1898
01:23:42,125 --> 01:23:44,750
[ASAKURA]
Oh, look at that. All clean.

1899
01:23:44,833 --> 01:23:47,666
Thank you so much for helping
me reach all the high places.

1900
01:23:47,750 --> 01:23:49,750
I couldn't have
done it without you.

1901
01:23:49,833 --> 01:23:53,541
Okay, everyone. Let's take a
break now and have some lunch.

1902
01:23:53,625 --> 01:23:56,125
Mr. Kimidori, would you
help me cook something?

1903
01:23:56,208 --> 01:23:57,708
[MR. KIMIDORI]
You got it.

1904
01:23:59,250 --> 01:24:01,250
Okay, time for
the salt and pepper.

1905
01:24:01,333 --> 01:24:03,041
[MR. KIMIDORI]
Coming up.

1906
01:24:03,125 --> 01:24:05,000
Why thank you, Mr. Kimidori.

1907
01:24:05,083 --> 01:24:07,833
Having you around makes
the day go smooth.

1908
01:24:12,125 --> 01:24:14,208
[ASAKURA]
That's it! We're done.

1909
01:24:14,291 --> 01:24:15,875
You don't know how
much I appreciate

1910
01:24:15,958 --> 01:24:17,833
all the help you gave me today.

1911
01:24:17,916 --> 01:24:19,083
Hm?

1912
01:24:19,166 --> 01:24:21,333
I was going to ask you
earlier, Mr. Kimidori.

1913
01:24:21,416 --> 01:24:23,541
Why are you inside that?

1914
01:24:24,833 --> 01:24:27,541
You will understand
once you get into this.

1915
01:24:27,625 --> 01:24:28,541
[ASAKURA]
Oh.

1916
01:24:28,625 --> 01:24:30,666
[ASAKURA laughs]

1917
01:24:53,666 --> 01:24:55,083
[HARUHI]
Here we g--!

1918
01:24:55,166 --> 01:24:56,625
[HARUHI groaning]

1919
01:25:03,208 --> 01:25:04,458
[HARUHI]
Hi everyone!

1920
01:25:04,541 --> 01:25:06,791
Thanks for tuning in to
another fun-filled episode

1921
01:25:06,875 --> 01:25:10,166
of my talk show.
Haruhi Suzumiya's Room.

1922
01:25:10,250 --> 01:25:12,375
Let's get things started
by introducing

1923
01:25:12,458 --> 01:25:13,583
our guest today.

1924
01:25:13,666 --> 01:25:15,958
Okay. He calls himself
a horrible virus.

1925
01:25:16,041 --> 01:25:17,583
With contagious laughter.

1926
01:25:17,666 --> 01:25:18,791
Please meet Kyon.

1927
01:25:18,875 --> 01:25:20,000
That's a lie!

1928
01:25:20,083 --> 01:25:21,708
I'd never call myself
something like that!

1929
01:25:21,791 --> 01:25:25,000
Whoa! He just got here,
and now he's tearing into me.

1930
01:25:25,083 --> 01:25:27,458
What should I do? I can't
keep up with him!

1931
01:25:27,541 --> 01:25:30,291
You haven't got this whole
TV-hosting thing down yet.

1932
01:25:30,375 --> 01:25:32,166
Yeah. I'll figure it out though.

1933
01:25:32,250 --> 01:25:34,375
Miss Waitress.
Can we have two coffees?

1934
01:25:34,458 --> 01:25:35,250
Okay.

1935
01:25:35,333 --> 01:25:36,500
What's with the waitress?

1936
01:25:36,583 --> 01:25:38,166
I thought this was
supposed to be your room.

1937
01:25:38,250 --> 01:25:40,333
Let's get back to
the show or somethin'.

1938
01:25:40,416 --> 01:25:41,625
[KYON]
You're too laid back.

1939
01:25:41,708 --> 01:25:42,875
Very well, Kyon.

1940
01:25:42,958 --> 01:25:44,375
How 'bout we start the
ball rolling with a few

1941
01:25:44,458 --> 01:25:45,708
hard-hitting questions?

1942
01:25:45,791 --> 01:25:48,166
[KYON]
Okay. Shoot.

1943
01:25:52,125 --> 01:25:53,875
I can't think of
anything to ask you.

1944
01:25:53,958 --> 01:25:55,083
[KYON]
You're kidding!

1945
01:25:55,166 --> 01:25:57,333
Pretend you never met me
before or something!

1946
01:25:57,416 --> 01:25:59,000
At least make some
kind of effort

1947
01:25:59,083 --> 01:26:00,500
to ask me a question, woman!

1948
01:26:00,583 --> 01:26:03,833
The kids today have such short
fuses, don't they? Scary.

1949
01:26:03,916 --> 01:26:05,041
[KYON]
Oh, come on.

1950
01:26:05,125 --> 01:26:07,583
You're way scarier than I am.
Get serious.

1951
01:26:07,666 --> 01:26:09,000
Okay, fine.

1952
01:26:09,083 --> 01:26:11,541
I guess you're right,
I wasn't taking it seriously.

1953
01:26:11,625 --> 01:26:13,833
I promise I'll be
serious from now on.

1954
01:26:13,916 --> 01:26:15,416
It's about time.
Let's do this.

1955
01:26:15,500 --> 01:26:16,583
Okay! Here we go.

1956
01:26:16,666 --> 01:26:18,458
I'm gonna take my
show so seriously,

1957
01:26:18,541 --> 01:26:20,875
I won't let our guests
in a word in edgewise.

1958
01:26:20,958 --> 01:26:23,333
Then it's not a talk show!
It's a monologue.

1959
01:26:23,416 --> 01:26:24,666
Yeah, sure. Whatever.

1960
01:26:24,750 --> 01:26:26,583
Our next guest is a person
who's a very good friend

1961
01:26:26,666 --> 01:26:27,791
of What's-his-name's,

1962
01:26:27,875 --> 01:26:29,125
Miss Yuki Nagato!

1963
01:26:29,208 --> 01:26:30,458
You haven't asked me anything

1964
01:26:30,541 --> 01:26:32,041
and you're bringing
out another guest?!

1965
01:26:32,125 --> 01:26:33,208
Hello.

1966
01:26:33,291 --> 01:26:35,208
Okay, Yuki. Do you
have any interesting,

1967
01:26:35,291 --> 01:26:37,916
gossip-y stories to tell
the audience about Kyon?

1968
01:26:38,000 --> 01:26:39,625
Yes. I might.

1969
01:26:42,625 --> 01:26:43,833
There really aren't any.

1970
01:26:43,916 --> 01:26:45,375
[KYON]
Ha! I knew it!

1971
01:26:45,458 --> 01:26:47,875
Kyon, you're the boring-est
guest I've ever had.

1972
01:26:47,958 --> 01:26:49,875
[KYON]
Now you're blaming the guest?

1973
01:26:49,958 --> 01:26:52,791
Okay, Kyon. Help us
out here and tell us a story.

1974
01:26:52,875 --> 01:26:53,833
Just make somethin' up.

1975
01:26:53,916 --> 01:26:56,666
It's up to me to do it?!
Let's see...

1976
01:26:56,750 --> 01:26:58,166
Mikuru can't help you now,

1977
01:26:58,250 --> 01:27:00,375
'cause it's the third time
we've done this window bit.

1978
01:27:00,458 --> 01:27:02,958
Okay! I'm sorry! I don't
have any stories to tell!

1979
01:27:03,041 --> 01:27:05,541
And stop eating!

1980
01:27:05,625 --> 01:27:06,583
I didn't wanna go there,

1981
01:27:06,666 --> 01:27:08,333
but I guess I don't
have a choice.

1982
01:27:08,416 --> 01:27:10,250
I'll have to whip out
my secret weapon.

1983
01:27:10,333 --> 01:27:11,875
Secret what?

1984
01:27:12,375 --> 01:27:14,708
I've prepared a scenario
utilizing every contact

1985
01:27:14,791 --> 01:27:16,833
in my wide-ranging
network of contacts.

1986
01:27:16,916 --> 01:27:19,333
[KYON] Things are gonna
get complicated now.

1987
01:27:19,416 --> 01:27:21,458
It's an amazing story about
a group of friends

1988
01:27:21,541 --> 01:27:23,541
who are aliens, time
travelers, and ESPers.

1989
01:27:23,625 --> 01:27:26,333
It's everything you could ever
possibly want in a show.

1990
01:27:26,416 --> 01:27:28,750
Okay! Now that's what
I'm talkin' about!

1991
01:27:28,833 --> 01:27:30,208
Good job, Number 2!

1992
01:27:30,291 --> 01:27:32,083
[KOIZUMI]
Oh, I'm just happy to help.

1993
01:27:32,166 --> 01:27:34,208
[KYON]
I live that story every day!

1994
01:27:34,291 --> 01:27:36,666
Okay, Kyon. Go ahead
and pick a scenario.

1995
01:27:36,750 --> 01:27:37,666
And don't peek!

1996
01:27:37,750 --> 01:27:40,041
[KYON]
Just... pick one blind?

1997
01:27:40,125 --> 01:27:42,458
Okay. This one.

1998
01:27:43,250 --> 01:27:45,083
This has nothing to do with me!

1999
01:27:45,166 --> 01:27:45,791
Yum.

2000
01:27:45,875 --> 01:27:46,916
[KYON]
Stop eating!

2001
01:28:06,833 --> 01:28:08,250
[HARUHI]
Here we g--!

2002
01:28:08,333 --> 01:28:09,625
[HARUHI groans]

2003
01:28:17,541 --> 01:28:19,583
[ASAKURA]
Oh, this rain!

2004
01:28:19,666 --> 01:28:20,791
Getting laundry to dry

2005
01:28:20,875 --> 01:28:23,250
in weather like this
is next to impossible!

2006
01:28:23,333 --> 01:28:25,833
My street clothes are
never gonna dry out!

2007
01:28:25,916 --> 01:28:27,833
[MR. KIMIDORI] Aah, I was
wondering why you're

2008
01:28:27,916 --> 01:28:29,875
wearing your school
uniform today.

2009
01:28:29,958 --> 01:28:31,291
What memories!

2010
01:28:31,375 --> 01:28:33,958
The last time I wore it
seems like forever ago!

2011
01:28:34,041 --> 01:28:36,791
I had a purpose back then,
a reason for being.

2012
01:28:36,875 --> 01:28:38,208
I could reach door knobs.

2013
01:28:38,291 --> 01:28:39,833
[MR. KIMIDORI]
Sorry, but you're turning this

2014
01:28:39,916 --> 01:28:41,458
into a flashback episode.

2015
01:28:41,541 --> 01:28:42,458
Let's not go there.

2016
01:28:42,541 --> 01:28:43,750
[ASAKURA]
Come on, just this once!

2017
01:28:43,833 --> 01:28:45,375
[MR. KIMIDORI]
Sorry, no.

2018
01:28:45,458 --> 01:28:46,791
[NAGATO]
I'm home.

2019
01:28:46,875 --> 01:28:48,541
[ASAKURA] Whoa! What happened
to you, Miss Nagato?!

2020
01:28:48,625 --> 01:28:50,250
[MR. KIMIDORI]
Yeah, you're drenched!

2021
01:28:50,333 --> 01:28:54,083
[NAGATO] On my way home,
a car splashed water on me.

2022
01:28:54,166 --> 01:28:55,333
[NAGATO]
Ahh!

2023
01:28:55,416 --> 01:28:56,458
[MR. KIMIDORI]
That's terrible, Miss Nagato.

2024
01:28:56,541 --> 01:28:57,708
You could've dodged
the water, though.

2025
01:28:57,791 --> 01:28:59,125
Why didn't you?

2026
01:28:59,208 --> 01:29:02,083
My priority was keeping my
laptop out of harm's way.

2027
01:29:02,166 --> 01:29:03,083
[ASAKURA]
Get out of those wet clothes,

2028
01:29:03,166 --> 01:29:05,125
and a take a nice, hot shower.

2029
01:29:06,708 --> 01:29:07,500
That was refreshing.

2030
01:29:07,583 --> 01:29:08,833
[ASAKURA screams]

2031
01:29:08,916 --> 01:29:10,833
I'm sorry, Miss Nagato.

2032
01:29:10,916 --> 01:29:14,000
I did laundry today and all
your clothes are still wet.

2033
01:29:14,083 --> 01:29:15,125
[NAGATO]
Oh...

2034
01:29:15,208 --> 01:29:17,041
Don't worry, I'll handle it.

2035
01:29:17,125 --> 01:29:18,250
[MR. KIMIDORI]
I know what you're up to.

2036
01:29:18,333 --> 01:29:19,666
Very clever.

2037
01:29:19,750 --> 01:29:20,833
[NAGATO]
Water balloon mode.

2038
01:29:20,916 --> 01:29:22,666
[ASAKURA screeches]

2039
01:29:22,750 --> 01:29:23,958
[MR. KIMIDORI]
I can explain.

2040
01:29:24,041 --> 01:29:25,916
Water balloon mode
is a process where

2041
01:29:26,000 --> 01:29:28,208
Miss Nagato collects all
the moisture in the air

2042
01:29:28,291 --> 01:29:30,041
and transfers it into my body.

2043
01:29:30,125 --> 01:29:32,208
Doing that will remove
the humidity from the air

2044
01:29:32,291 --> 01:29:34,583
and the clothes will
dry more quickly!

2045
01:29:34,666 --> 01:29:37,541
And I get to transform
into the giant ultra-dog

2046
01:29:37,625 --> 01:29:39,125
I've always wanted to be!

2047
01:29:39,208 --> 01:29:41,833
[ASAKURA] I hate to say this,
but you just got fatter is all.

2048
01:29:41,916 --> 01:29:44,458
And be careful, don't get
too excited or else--

2049
01:29:44,541 --> 01:29:45,291
[MR. KIMIDORI screams]

2050
01:29:45,375 --> 01:29:46,416
[ASAKURA]
I told you so!

2051
01:29:46,500 --> 01:29:48,583
[MR. KIMIDORI]
I know... Sorry.

2052
01:29:53,083 --> 01:29:54,083
[ASAKURA sighs]

2053
01:29:55,833 --> 01:29:57,583
[ASAKURA]
Aw...

2054
01:29:57,666 --> 01:29:59,666
This is so boring!

2055
01:29:59,750 --> 01:30:01,458
After we finish all the chores,

2056
01:30:01,541 --> 01:30:03,750
there's nothing to do except
wait for Miss Nagato

2057
01:30:03,833 --> 01:30:05,625
to come home.
I hate to complain,

2058
01:30:05,708 --> 01:30:08,666
but I wish we had something
to entertain ourselves with.

2059
01:30:08,750 --> 01:30:10,875
[MR. KIMIDORI] If we could
go outside by ourselves,

2060
01:30:10,958 --> 01:30:12,833
we wouldn't have this problem.

2061
01:30:12,916 --> 01:30:13,583
Huh?

2062
01:30:13,666 --> 01:30:14,458
[ASAKURA]
Hm?

2063
01:30:14,541 --> 01:30:15,958
Is everything okay?

2064
01:30:16,041 --> 01:30:18,708
[MR. KIMIDORI]
I just remembered something.

2065
01:30:18,791 --> 01:30:22,541
[NAGATO] If the two of
you get bored, open this.

2066
01:30:22,625 --> 01:30:24,750
[MR. KIMIDORI] That's what
she said, and she gave me this.

2067
01:30:24,833 --> 01:30:27,416
Uh-huh... A mysterious box.

2068
01:30:27,500 --> 01:30:28,708
[MR. KIMIDORI]
Correct.

2069
01:30:28,791 --> 01:30:30,708
You know there's something
totally suspicious

2070
01:30:30,791 --> 01:30:32,041
about this thing.

2071
01:30:32,125 --> 01:30:34,083
[MR. KIMIDORI] Whatever.
We might as well open it.

2072
01:30:34,166 --> 01:30:35,250
Be careful!

2073
01:30:35,333 --> 01:30:36,375
--[MR. KIMIDORI screams]
--[ASAKURA gasps]

2074
01:30:37,958 --> 01:30:41,875
[beep]

2075
01:30:41,958 --> 01:30:43,125
[MR. KIMIDORI]
Um...

2076
01:30:43,208 --> 01:30:45,250
I'm hearing a beeping
sound coming from it.

2077
01:30:45,333 --> 01:30:47,333
Is this thing what
I think it is?

2078
01:30:47,416 --> 01:30:48,875
[laughs nervously]

2079
01:30:48,958 --> 01:30:50,083
No way.

2080
01:30:51,333 --> 01:30:52,791
[MR. KIMIDORI]
Mm-hm?

2081
01:30:52,875 --> 01:30:55,583
That's your typical two-wire
scenario and a pair of scissors.

2082
01:30:55,666 --> 01:30:57,541
[ASAKURA whimpers]

2083
01:30:59,250 --> 01:31:00,500
Oh, I get it.

2084
01:31:00,583 --> 01:31:02,250
To disarm it, I'm gonna
have to use these scissors

2085
01:31:02,333 --> 01:31:03,916
to cut one of the wires.

2086
01:31:04,000 --> 01:31:05,625
[MR. KIMIDORI]
Uh. Good guess.

2087
01:31:05,708 --> 01:31:07,000
This is fake.

2088
01:31:07,083 --> 01:31:09,458
Nothing's gonna happen to us
if I cut the wrong wire.

2089
01:31:09,541 --> 01:31:12,250
[MR. KIMIDORI] Uh, yeah... It's
just a toy to keep us occupied.

2090
01:31:12,333 --> 01:31:13,458
It can't be real.

2091
01:31:13,541 --> 01:31:15,416
I mean, she wouldn't
do something like that.

2092
01:31:15,500 --> 01:31:18,791
[BOTH laugh]

2093
01:31:18,875 --> 01:31:21,333
It really looks like
a real bomb though!

2094
01:31:21,416 --> 01:31:22,750
[MR. KIMIDORI cries]

2095
01:31:22,833 --> 01:31:23,708
[MR. KIMIDORI]
If this thing explodes,

2096
01:31:23,791 --> 01:31:24,958
I don't want you getting hurt.

2097
01:31:25,041 --> 01:31:26,916
There's only one
thing for me to do.

2098
01:31:27,000 --> 01:31:28,541
[ASAKURA] Mr. Kimidori,
what are you doing?!

2099
01:31:28,625 --> 01:31:31,083
[MR. KIMIDORI] If anyone's gonna
get blown up, it's gonna be me!

2100
01:31:31,166 --> 01:31:33,750
[ASAKURA] No, Mr. Kimidori!
I don't want that!

2101
01:31:33,833 --> 01:31:35,541
Come back here!

2102
01:31:38,333 --> 01:31:40,583
[ASAKURA crying]

2103
01:31:40,666 --> 01:31:41,625
[beep]

2104
01:31:42,583 --> 01:31:46,833
[ASAKURA]
Mr. Kimidori!

2105
01:31:46,916 --> 01:31:48,291
[MR. KIMIDORI panting]

2106
01:31:48,375 --> 01:31:49,083
[ASAKURA laughs]

2107
01:31:49,166 --> 01:31:50,541
Come back!

2108
01:31:50,625 --> 01:31:52,708
[MR. KIMIDORI] Aw, come on.
Don't let it getcha down.

2109
01:31:52,791 --> 01:31:57,000
How about Mr. Kimidori? It is
the color of my body, after all.

2110
01:31:57,083 --> 01:31:58,541
The light's fading...

2111
01:31:58,625 --> 01:32:01,958
I want to be cremated and my
ashes scattered to the wind.

2112
01:32:02,041 --> 01:32:03,875
[chuckles] Guess who?

2113
01:32:03,958 --> 01:32:05,875
I bet you're
surprised to see me.

2114
01:32:05,958 --> 01:32:08,000
Okay, time for
the salt and pepper.

2115
01:32:08,083 --> 01:32:10,208
[MR. KIMIDORI]
Coming up.

2116
01:32:10,291 --> 01:32:13,250
Miss Asakura... Farewell.

2117
01:32:14,625 --> 01:32:17,708
[ASAKURA screams]

2118
01:32:23,333 --> 01:32:24,333
I am home.

2119
01:32:24,416 --> 01:32:25,791
[ASAKURA]
Oh! You're back!

2120
01:32:25,875 --> 01:32:28,750
[BOTH]
Welcome home, Miss Nagato!

2121
01:32:28,833 --> 01:32:30,000
Why is he burnt?

2122
01:32:30,083 --> 01:32:31,250
We were sorta bored,

2123
01:32:31,333 --> 01:32:33,791
so we pretended we were
a bomb disposal unit.

2124
01:32:33,875 --> 01:32:36,750
[MR. KIMIDORI] My performance
was more method than usual.

2125
01:34:32,541 --> 01:34:35,375
[BOTH groan]

2126
01:34:35,458 --> 01:34:36,458
[KYON]
Okay...

2127
01:34:36,541 --> 01:34:38,916
What the hell was that?

2128
01:34:39,000 --> 01:34:40,791
[HARUHI]
When's it gonna stop?

2129
01:34:40,875 --> 01:34:42,625
It sucks when it
keeps raining like this

2130
01:34:42,708 --> 01:34:44,333
because we can't go outside.

2131
01:34:44,416 --> 01:34:45,333
Right, Mikuru?

2132
01:34:45,416 --> 01:34:46,875
You have a point there.

2133
01:34:46,958 --> 01:34:48,041
Even when it's not raining,

2134
01:34:48,125 --> 01:34:49,875
we're always
hanging out in here.

2135
01:34:49,958 --> 01:34:51,625
[HARUHI]
Really? No, we don't.

2136
01:34:51,708 --> 01:34:53,333
[KYON] We spend more
than half of our time

2137
01:34:53,416 --> 01:34:55,041
in this room, playing games.

2138
01:34:55,125 --> 01:34:56,291
[HARUHI]
Hmm...

2139
01:34:56,375 --> 01:34:58,666
But there's a different
reason for that, Kyon.

2140
01:34:58,750 --> 01:35:01,375
When the weather's nice, we
could go outdoors if we wanted!

2141
01:35:01,458 --> 01:35:03,375
But we stay inside
'cause we choose to!

2142
01:35:03,458 --> 01:35:05,000
[KYON]
She's hopeless!

2143
01:35:05,083 --> 01:35:06,583
[HARUHI]
I know...

2144
01:35:06,666 --> 01:35:09,750
We're gonna come up with some
new ideas for outfits to wear!

2145
01:35:09,833 --> 01:35:11,041
[KYON]
First, why?

2146
01:35:11,125 --> 01:35:13,291
Second, what're you
gonna make us wear?

2147
01:35:13,375 --> 01:35:14,916
I wasn't talking about us.

2148
01:35:15,000 --> 01:35:18,333
We're brainstorming
costumes for Mikuru!

2149
01:35:18,416 --> 01:35:19,750
[KYON]
Uh...

2150
01:35:19,833 --> 01:35:22,041
--[MIKURU screaming]
--[HARUHI laughing]

2151
01:35:22,125 --> 01:35:23,541
[MIKURU whimpering]

2152
01:35:23,625 --> 01:35:26,291
[HARUHI] We're gonna use
this board for our designs.

2153
01:35:26,375 --> 01:35:29,333
First, I'm gonna sketch a
template version of Mikuru.

2154
01:35:29,416 --> 01:35:32,500
Oh, I get it. Then we
draw our designs on top.

2155
01:35:32,583 --> 01:35:34,041
[BOTH]
Uh...

2156
01:35:34,125 --> 01:35:35,000
Is that her?

2157
01:35:35,083 --> 01:35:36,583
I guess...

2158
01:35:36,666 --> 01:35:37,916
I was drawing her from memory.

2159
01:35:38,000 --> 01:35:39,958
I don't know why it
came out like that.

2160
01:35:40,041 --> 01:35:41,333
You don't have to
use your memory

2161
01:35:41,416 --> 01:35:43,375
when your subject's hanging
right in front of you.

2162
01:35:43,458 --> 01:35:46,000
Okay, this time,
I'll look at her and draw.

2163
01:35:46,083 --> 01:35:47,041
[MIKURU whimpers]

2164
01:35:47,125 --> 01:35:48,291
[HARUHI]
Hm...

2165
01:35:48,375 --> 01:35:49,000
Mm-hm.

2166
01:35:49,083 --> 01:35:50,833
[MIKURU whimpers]

2167
01:35:52,291 --> 01:35:53,625
[KYON]
You just added the rope!

2168
01:35:53,708 --> 01:35:54,958
[HARUHI]
Huh?!

2169
01:35:55,041 --> 01:35:56,958
Hey, guys!
Is Mikuru around?

2170
01:35:57,041 --> 01:35:59,875
Yes! I'm up here!
What is it, Miss Tsuruya?

2171
01:35:59,958 --> 01:36:01,083
[TSURUYA]
Whoa!

2172
01:36:01,166 --> 01:36:03,000
Looks like something
interesting's going on!

2173
01:36:03,083 --> 01:36:05,166
Could I borrow your
notes from maths class?

2174
01:36:05,250 --> 01:36:06,375
[MIKURU]
Sure.

2175
01:36:06,458 --> 01:36:08,333
I'd get them, but I
can't move right now.

2176
01:36:08,416 --> 01:36:10,416
They're in my bag,
so help yourself.

2177
01:36:10,500 --> 01:36:11,416
Cool, thanks!

2178
01:36:11,500 --> 01:36:12,666
[KYON]
Well, how 'bout this?

2179
01:36:12,750 --> 01:36:14,416
[HARUHI]
That's not right, you dummy!

2180
01:36:14,500 --> 01:36:16,625
There! It's supposed
to be like that!

2181
01:36:16,708 --> 01:36:18,166
[TSURUYA]
What's with all the commotion?

2182
01:36:18,250 --> 01:36:19,666
You guys okay over there?

2183
01:36:19,750 --> 01:36:21,875
Hi, Miss Tsuruya.
Good timing.

2184
01:36:21,958 --> 01:36:24,333
We got stuck.
We need you!

2185
01:36:24,416 --> 01:36:25,541
I went off on a tangent,

2186
01:36:25,625 --> 01:36:27,833
and sort of forgot
what we were doing.

2187
01:36:27,916 --> 01:36:29,500
[KYON]
We're so lost right now,

2188
01:36:29,583 --> 01:36:31,583
we need help
getting back on track.

2189
01:36:31,666 --> 01:36:33,958
[TSURUYA] Are you guys tryin'
to make a monster movie?

2190
01:36:34,041 --> 01:36:35,208
Good try, but no.

2191
01:36:35,291 --> 01:36:37,291
You're way off,
but that's a good idea!

2192
01:36:37,375 --> 01:36:40,708
I know! We'll make our
second movie a monster movie!

2193
01:36:40,791 --> 01:36:42,083
[KYON]
Huh?!

2194
01:36:42,166 --> 01:36:43,291
[KYON]
They explained...

2195
01:36:43,375 --> 01:36:45,791
Uh-huh... Mikuru's
getting a new outfit.

2196
01:36:45,875 --> 01:36:48,666
You know, that's a pretty
cool idea for a project!

2197
01:36:48,750 --> 01:36:50,458
Tell you what,
guys, count me in!

2198
01:36:50,541 --> 01:36:52,958
This is gonna be
so awesome now!

2199
01:36:53,041 --> 01:36:54,375
Watch a learn!

2200
01:36:54,458 --> 01:36:56,708
My Tsuruya-style portrait
technique is so realistic,

2201
01:36:56,791 --> 01:36:58,541
it's like you're looking
at a photograph!

2202
01:36:58,625 --> 01:37:01,250
Stand back 'cause it's time
to do some drawing!

2203
01:37:01,333 --> 01:37:02,208
Hya!

2204
01:37:02,291 --> 01:37:04,166
Hah!

2205
01:37:04,250 --> 01:37:05,208
[BOTH gasp]

2206
01:37:11,125 --> 01:37:12,875
[ALL]
Uh...

2207
01:37:13,500 --> 01:37:14,666
[KYON]
You gotta be kidding.

2208
01:37:14,750 --> 01:37:16,916
[TSURUYA]
Huh?

2209
01:37:17,000 --> 01:37:18,916
[NAGATO] This room is currently
under the influence

2210
01:37:19,000 --> 01:37:21,041
of Haruhi Suzumiya's powers.

2211
01:37:21,125 --> 01:37:23,541
Therefore, any attempt
at accurate reproduction

2212
01:37:23,625 --> 01:37:26,375
using artistic techniques
has been neutralized.

2213
01:37:26,458 --> 01:37:27,625
[KYON]
Um...

2214
01:37:27,708 --> 01:37:29,125
This drawing stuff
isn't really working out,

2215
01:37:29,208 --> 01:37:31,875
so maybe we should quit for now.

2216
01:37:31,958 --> 01:37:33,291
Yeah, you got a point there.

2217
01:37:33,375 --> 01:37:35,666
You're right. We should
try doin' somethin' else.

2218
01:37:35,750 --> 01:37:37,416
Something else like what?

2219
01:37:37,500 --> 01:37:39,750
Miss Tsuruya? You know, right?

2220
01:37:39,833 --> 01:37:42,250
[TSURUYA chuckles] Time to
break out our bag of tricks.

2221
01:37:42,333 --> 01:37:43,500
[BOTH laugh]

2222
01:37:43,583 --> 01:37:44,500
[MIKURU gasps]

2223
01:37:44,583 --> 01:37:46,666
Stay away!
You both look so evil!

2224
01:37:46,750 --> 01:37:49,166
[MIKURU screams]

2225
01:37:49,250 --> 01:37:50,166
[HARUHI]
All done!

2226
01:37:50,250 --> 01:37:52,041
[TSURUYA]
Yup! She looks awesome!

2227
01:37:52,125 --> 01:37:53,458
[BOTH]
It's her new monster costume!

2228
01:37:53,541 --> 01:37:54,750
I freaking knew it!

2229
01:37:54,833 --> 01:37:56,875
We were supposed to
make a new outfit for her!

2230
01:37:56,958 --> 01:37:58,291
[BOTH]
Oh...

2231
01:37:58,375 --> 01:37:59,958
[BOTH] It's her new outfit!
What do you think?

2232
01:38:00,041 --> 01:38:01,041
[KYON]
You just rephrased it!

2233
01:38:01,125 --> 01:38:03,041
That's still a
monster movie costume!

2234
01:38:03,125 --> 01:38:05,166
Now all she needs is
a monster to fight!

2235
01:38:05,250 --> 01:38:07,208
Have you done any
casting for it?

2236
01:38:07,291 --> 01:38:08,375
Not yet.

2237
01:38:08,458 --> 01:38:10,791
I wonder who could
play the rival monster.

2238
01:38:10,875 --> 01:38:12,500
[HARUHI gasps]
You wanna do it, Yuki?

2239
01:38:12,583 --> 01:38:13,875
Absolutely.

2240
01:38:13,958 --> 01:38:15,875
Don't you even wanna
think about it first?

2241
01:38:15,958 --> 01:38:18,333
I absolutely want to do it.

2242
01:38:18,416 --> 01:38:20,791
Remember, I have
done this before.

2243
01:38:20,875 --> 01:38:22,000
[KYON]
Oh, yeah.

2244
01:38:22,083 --> 01:38:24,000
I have to prepare for battle!

2245
01:38:24,083 --> 01:38:27,208
[KYON]
S-Sure. Break a leg.

2246
01:38:30,333 --> 01:38:31,750
[NAGATO roars]

2247
01:38:31,833 --> 01:38:35,625
--[MIKURU screams]
--[HARUHI laughing]

2248
01:38:40,625 --> 01:38:43,250
[KYON]
Hm? Are you okay over there?

2249
01:38:43,333 --> 01:38:46,083
You didn't get involved in
any of today's craziness.

2250
01:38:46,166 --> 01:38:49,541
